Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.91,0:16:25.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,我儿子唯一的一项才能就是...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ As Mr. Greenleaf]The only talent my son has...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.08,0:16:28.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,花钱如流水.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}is for cashing his allowance.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.71,0:16:33.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么?   -哦,我喜欢航行.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What ?  - Oh, I like to sail.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.12,0:16:35.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,相信我,我喜欢航行.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Believe me,I love to sail.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.09,0:16:37.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 真的,我造船.   - 住嘴!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Instead, I make boats.  - Stop !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.17,0:16:39.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 其他人乘它们远航.   - 够了!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Other people sail them.  - It's too much !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.59,0:16:41.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,你让我浑身起鸡皮疙瘩.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're making all the hairs on my neck stand up.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.67,0:16:45.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,是啊.爵士.哦.爵士.让我们看看.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, yes. Jazz.Oh, jazz. Let's face it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.14,0:16:48.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,那不过是,那不过是--那不过是靡靡之音罢了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It’s just, uh--It’s just insolent noise.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.77,0:16:50.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,好像他真来了一样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I feel like he's here.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.85,0:16:55.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,-太可怕了,就像那个老混蛋真来了似的.   -太棒了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Horrible, like the old bastard's here.  - Good.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.13,0:16:56.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,-太棒了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That's brilliant.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.15,0:16:58.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,-太棒了!你是怎么认识他的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Brilliant !How do you know him ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.07,0:17:00.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢，我和他在纽约见过面.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, I met him in New York.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.90,0:17:03.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉!玛吉,真是太吓人了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge !Marge, this is scary.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.81,0:17:05.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,你得来听听.见过我父亲,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You've got to hear this.Meet my father,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.57,0:17:07.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,赫伯特·理查德·格林立夫一世.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Herbert Richard Greenleaf 1.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.87,0:17:11.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你迪克的眼光不错.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Pleasure to meet you.Dickie's made a fine catch.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.83,0:17:14.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,-真不可思议!   -我知道埃米莉一定也是这么想的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Uncanny !  - I know Emily thinks so.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.42,0:17:16.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我弄不明白.   -太不可思议了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I don't get it.  - It's uncanny.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.75,0:17:19.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,你能不能考虑去一趟意大利，汤姆,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Could you ever conceive of going to Italy, Tom,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.96,0:17:22.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后,嗯,把他带回来?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and, uh, bringing him back ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.97,0:17:25.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,-什么?   -我会付给你酬劳.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What ?  - I'd pay you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.05,0:17:27.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你愿意去意大利,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}If you would go to Italy,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.80,0:17:31.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,劝我儿子回家来，我会付给你1000美金.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}persuade my son to come home,I'd pay you a thousand dollars.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.89,0:17:35.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,我绝不会回去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Dickie]I'm never going back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.94,0:17:38.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,还雇人大老远地跑这儿来...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}To actually hire somebody to come all the way here...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.73,0:17:40.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,把我拉回去...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}to drag me back home...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.73,0:17:42.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,肯定是神经有点毛病了，是不是?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Got to be a little insane, doesn't he ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.94,0:17:45.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你好,福斯托.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Ciao, Fausto.- [ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.45,0:17:51.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,-这位是汤姆.   -你好,汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- This is Tom.  - Ciao, Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.99,0:17:54.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.48,0:17:56.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我绝不会回去的.   -不过,我想...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I'm never going back.  - No, I think...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.79,0:17:58.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,你母亲,她的病,我觉得那样有点...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Your mother, her illness,I think that's...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:01.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,这和我妈妈一点关系都没有.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's got nothing to do with my mother.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.01,0:18:05.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,她有白血病...这更让我厌烦他.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}She's had leukem...This is what makes me boil about him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.76,0:18:09.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,是他想让我回去.是他想让我回去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He wants me back.He wants me back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.43,0:18:11.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,-这和我母亲一点关系都没有   -你看，我不明白...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- It's got nothing to do with my mother.  - Look, I don't know...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.85,0:18:13.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,回去.回纽约去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Go back.Go back to New York.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.85,0:18:15.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,要么就给他打个电话,如果你能找得到可用的电话,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Or call him, if you can find a telephone that works,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.98,0:18:20.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,告诉他就是野马也不能把我拉回他跟他那个船坞那儿去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and tell him wild horses wouldn't drag me back to him or his shipyard.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.94,0:18:25.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,-嗨，汤姆.   -嗨.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Hi, Tom.  - Hi.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.03,0:18:28.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉，汤姆来告别.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, Tom's saying good-bye.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.41,0:18:30.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢，我来了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, I'll come down.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.95,0:18:34.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么,嗯,你和我爸爸说过了吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So, uh, did you speak to my father ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.45,0:18:36.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,你是对的...关于电话.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, you were right...about the telephones.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.75,0:18:38.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我告诉过你.   - 根本连电话线都没有.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I told you.  - There are no lines.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.75,0:18:41.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 没问题.  - 这就是意大利.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- There's some problem. - That's Italy.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.56,0:18:47.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,汤姆.你要走了?你有什么打算?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tom. You're off ?What are your plans ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.43,0:18:49.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦，回去,我想,越慢越好.噢!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, back, I suppose,as slow as I can. Oh !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.64,0:18:53.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,这个破包!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}This bag !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:58.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗨.你喜欢爵士.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hey.You like jazz.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.12,0:18:59.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,我爱爵士.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I love jazz.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.48,0:19:04.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是最好的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}This is the best.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.48,0:19:07.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,贝克尔,罗林斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Baker, Rollins.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.65,0:19:10.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉说她喜欢爵士,但是她以为格兰-米勒叫爵士.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge says she likes jazz,but she thinks Glenn Miller’s jazz.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.95,0:19:12.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我可从没那么说过!   -《伯德》.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I never said that ! - [Tom] Bird.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.99,0:19:15.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,这才是爵士.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That’s jazz.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.88,0:19:17.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,《伯德》? 问问我我的游艇叫什么名字.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Bird ? Ask me the name of my sailboat.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.66,0:19:19.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道.你的游艇叫什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know. What's the name of your sailboat ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.71,0:19:21.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,看啊!看啊!伯德!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Look ! Look !Bird !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.00,0:19:24.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,这太荒谬了.船是女性化的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Marge]Which is ridiculous. Boats are female.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.80,0:19:28.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,谁都知道你不能给一只船取个男人的名字.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Everyone knows you can't call a boat after a man.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.59,0:19:31.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 他不是男人，他是上帝.   -好,我们一起去那不勒斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- He's not a man. He's a god. - Okay, we're going to Naples.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.47,0:19:34.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,那儿有个俱乐部...也不算是个俱乐部,是个地下室.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There's a club...It's not a club, it's a cellar.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.14,0:19:37.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,-很烂.   -是的,很烂.你不一定要来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}-It's vile.  -Yes, it's vile. You don't have to come.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.14,0:19:39.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,太棒了. 太..太棒了.你会喜欢它的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's great. It's..It's great.You're gonna love it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.80,0:20:14.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}How are you ?{\c}
