Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.36,0:22:40.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 这儿...   - 你总是打印信件?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Here... - You always type your letters ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.04,0:22:45.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,-这儿应该是两个"T".   -我不会写,我也不会拼.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- That should be two T's. - I can't write, and I can't spell.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.58,0:22:48.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是一流教育赋予的特权.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's the privilege of a first-class education.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.54,0:22:50.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,你的房间在后面楼上.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Your room's upstairs at the back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.71,0:22:53.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想厄玛琳达已经整理好了床铺，厄玛琳达!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I think Ermalinda made up the bed. Ermalinda !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.41,0:22:55.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Both Speaking Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.01,0:22:58.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你真是太好了.   -别再提了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- This is so good of you. - Don't say it again.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.85,0:23:06.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在你是个双面间谍了，我们一起合谋来骗我父亲,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Now that you're a double agent and we're going to string my dad along,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.06,0:23:08.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,你说我们用你的佣金买辆车怎么样?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}what if we were to buy a car with your expense money ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.90,0:23:11.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 好啊.    - 太好了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Okay.   - Great.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.22,0:23:13.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.74,0:23:13.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你好,汤姆.   -你好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Hello, Tom.  - Hello.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.44,0:23:15.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉,玛吉,你说怎么样?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, Marge,what do you think ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.82,0:23:17.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,用我爸爸的钱买辆小车?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Little Ciquencento with my dad's money ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.07,0:23:20.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦，拜托，迪克.你连车都不会开.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, please, Dickie.You can't even drive a car.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.99,0:23:24.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你连车都不会开.   -我们现在需要的是个冰箱.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Tom] You can't even drive. - What we need urgently is an icebox.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.41,0:23:27.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么认为?同意我吧,我保证我们会成为终生的朋友.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What do you think ? Agree with me,and I'll be your friend for life.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.24,0:23:31.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我完全同意玛吉.  -嗯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I absolutely agree with Marge. - Hmm.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.92,0:23:34.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,冰箱.冰箱.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Icebox. Icebox.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.17,0:23:40.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Bell Tolling]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.60,0:23:48.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么,什么,他会搬来和你一起住?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Marge]So, what, is he gonna move in with you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.81,0:23:53.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,就一段时间.他能--他能让我发笑.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It'll just be for a little while.He can be-- He makes me laugh.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.57,0:23:57.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,-好吧,亲爱的.    -保证?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Okay, darling. - Promise you'd say ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.15,0:24:00.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,-不,我喜欢他.   -玛吉,你谁都喜欢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- No, I like him. - Marge, you like everybody.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.07,0:24:03.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,不喜欢你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Chuckles]Don't like you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.87,0:24:06.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,那我会搬去你那儿，你和汤姆一起住好了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Then I'll go to your place and you can move in with Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.71,0:24:17.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢他.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Imitating Marge ]I like him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.71,0:24:21.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉,你谁都喜欢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Imitating Dickie ]Marge, you like everybody.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.64,0:24:28.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,-不,我喜欢他.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Imitating Marge ]No, I like him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.64,0:24:33.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉,你谁都喜欢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Imitating Dickie ]Marge, you like everybody.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.56,0:24:37.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在你知道为什么舍伍德小姐总是会在早餐时出现.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Dickie] Now you'll find out why Miss Sherwood always shows up for breakfast.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.15,0:24:39.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是爱.是我的咖啡机.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's not love.It's my coffee machine.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.82,0:24:42.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,自从厄玛琳达教他怎样自己煮咖啡,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Marge] Ever since Ermalinda showed him how to make his own espresso,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.66,0:24:44.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,他就觉得自己是成人了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}he feels like quite the grownup.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.95,0:24:47.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,-是我买的咖啡机.   -噢,亲爱的,那杯是给我的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}-I bought the coffee machine.  -[Marge] Oh, darling, is that for me ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.83,0:24:50.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,这杯是给汤姆的, 因为他不会抱怨.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}This is for Tom, because he didn't complain.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.48,0:24:53.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,那戒指太美了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Tom] That ring is superb.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.12,0:24:55.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢,汤姆,我爱你.知道了吧?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, Tom, I love you.See ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.67,0:25:00.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,唔!我还得很郑重地发誓,决不取下它.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ooh ! I had to promise,capital "P," never to take it off.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.76,0:25:04.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,-要不然,我会把它送给你.  -是不是很棒? 我在那不勒斯淘到的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}-Otherwise, I'd give it to you. -Isn't it great ? I found it in Naples.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.14,0:25:06.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,我为了买下它整整还了两周的价.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I had to bargain for it for about two weeks.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.80,0:25:09.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,我希望它不便宜,玛吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I hope it wasn't cheap,Marge.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.68,0:25:12.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,-哦,是很便宜.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Oh, it was. - [ Chuckles ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.07,0:25:15.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,我得为弗朗西斯买件生日礼物，也许你能帮帮我.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I have to get a birthday present for Frances, so perhaps you could help me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.98,0:25:18.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,-谁是弗朗西斯?   -我的未婚妻.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Who's Frances ? - My fiancée.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.86,0:25:21.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,订婚了?你可真是出其不意啊,瑞普雷.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Engaged ?You're a dark horse, Ripley.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.78,0:25:23.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,-她是谁?    -你的父母见过她.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Who is she ?  - Your parents met her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.78,0:25:27.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,天啊.噢,我能想象.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, God.Oh, I can just imagine.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.74,0:25:29.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,"如果迪克能成家该多好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}"If only Dickie would settle down.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.99,0:25:32.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,每一对父母都该有个孙子不是吗?"\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Doesn't every parent deserve a grandchild ?"{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.16,0:25:35.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,天.决不.决不.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, God.Never. Never.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.04,0:25:39.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,我以你的戒指发誓，玛吉，我永远也不回去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I swear on your ring, Marge,I'm never going back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.71,0:25:42.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,-告诉我什么时候该拉.  -现在拉.拉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Tom ] Say when to pull. - [ Dickie ] Pull now. Pull.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.58,0:25:46.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,那不是在拉.我做错了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's not pulling.I'm doing it wrong.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.97,0:25:50.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,-现在好点了,嗯?  -好,好,好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Better now, huh ? - Okay, okay, okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.39,0:25:52.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,就由你来开船了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We'll make a sailor of you yet.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.39,0:25:54.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,你做得很不错.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're doing really well.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.81,0:25:58.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,-好了.酒吧时间.   -好,请.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- All right. Bar's open.  - Yes, please.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.11,0:26:01.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗨,我们能开船去威尼斯吗?   - 好啊.我爱威尼斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Hey, can we sail to Venice ?  - Sure. I love Venice.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.36,0:26:06.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,"看到威尼斯死而无憾."是吗? 要么应该是罗马?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}"See Venice and die."Isn't that right ? Or is it Rome ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.07,0:26:09.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,-是罗马吗?   -我得说是威尼斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Is it Rome ?  - I have to see Venice.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.24,0:26:13.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,你做了一些事情后便死而无憾了,不是吗?威尼斯就是其中之一\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You do something and die, don't you ?Okay. Venice is on the list.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.16,0:26:15.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,还有罗马.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And Rome.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.79,0:26:17.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,你会滑雪吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Do you ski ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.09,0:26:22.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,啊,不是吧,不是吧.别说真是这样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ah, no, no.Don't tell me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.92,0:26:26.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,你完了.这是接下来要做的一件事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're a lost cause.That's the next thing to deal with.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.60,0:26:28.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,圣诞节,我们打算去科尔蒂纳滑雪.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Christmas, we’re planning a skiing trip to Cortina.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.93,0:26:32.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,-很棒的滑雪.太棒了.玛吉.   -什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Excellent skiing. Excellent. Marge.  - Yes ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.43,0:26:35.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,不可思议.汤姆连滑雪都不会.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Unbelievable.Tom can't ski either.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.28,0:26:38.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我们还得再教他滑雪.   -谢谢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- We'll have to teach him that too.  - Thank you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.44,0:26:43.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,太掉价了,玛吉.这家伙有没有什么会的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Such low class, Marge.Does this guy know anything ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.74,0:26:45.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们还没快结婚真是幸事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Good thing we're not getting married soon.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.07,0:26:48.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,否则我们还得请汤姆和我们共度蜜月.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We'd have to invite Tom on our honeymoon.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.08,0:26:55.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,我恨纽约.恨拥挤的帕克大道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Marge] Oh, I hated New York.That whole Park Avenue crowd.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.08,0:26:57.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以我飞去巴黎打算专心写我的书.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So I fled to Paris to work on my book.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.12,0:27:00.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,我经常会去蒙特利尔的一家咖啡馆...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I was always going to this cafe in Monmartre...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.53,0:27:02.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,和让-让克一起.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}with Jean-Jaques.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.96,0:27:05.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克会演奏《我有趣的情人》\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And Dickie would play "My Funny Valentine."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.97,0:27:12.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,只是我后来才发现原来他就会那六首曲子.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It was only later that I found out he only knows about six songs.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.05,0:27:13.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过,我很想见见他,我想.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Anyway, I looked forward to seeing him, I suppose.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.76,0:27:17.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Speaking Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.99,0:27:37.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Men Chattering in Italian]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.08,0:27:43.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗨,嗨,格林立夫先生!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hey, hey, Signor Greenleaf !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.84,0:27:47.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,你七点还没到我那儿,汤姆和我打算私奔了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're not at my place by 7.:00,Tom and I are running off together.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.59,0:27:50.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,-好啊，很好.   -噢，迪克!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Okay, fine.  - [Man] Oh, Dickie !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.92,0:27:56.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Indistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.69,0:28:03.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,等会儿.等会儿.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, hold on.Hold on.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.74,0:28:07.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,希尔维那,希尔维那\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Silvana, Silvana{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.65,0:28:09.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,你让我微笑\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You make me smile{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.65,0:28:12.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,我得和你谈谈.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I need to talk to you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.86,0:28:15.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Continues]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.83,0:28:22.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你快把我的肋骨压断了!   -什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Dickie ] You're breaking my ribs !  - What ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.59,0:28:26.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,你快把我的肋骨压断了!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're breaking my ribs !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.57,0:28:31.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是请不要\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But don't{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.51,0:28:35.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,为我改变一丝一毫\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Change a hair for me{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.93,0:28:39.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Not if you care{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.06,0:28:42.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,真爱我\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}For me{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.52,0:28:49.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,留下,小瓦伦丁\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Stay, little Valentine{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.57,0:28:54.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,留下\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Stay{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.41,0:29:00.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,每一天\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Each day{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.46,0:29:07.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,都是情人节\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Is Valentine's Day{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.47,0:29:13.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ohh ![ Kisses ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.13,0:29:18.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,我都能干这只冰箱了,我太爱它了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I could fuck this icebox,I love it so much.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.85,0:29:23.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么，你在纽约是做什么的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So, what did you actually do in New York ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.48,0:29:26.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,四处弹钢琴.我告诉过你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Played piano in a few places.I told you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.74,0:29:29.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,好,那只是一份工作.你说过你有好几份工作.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, that's one job.You told me a lot of jobs.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.44,0:29:31.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,好几个地方.那就是好几份工作了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Few places.That's a few jobs.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.99,0:29:34.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,神秘的瑞普雷先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The mysterious Mr. Ripley.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.16,0:29:36.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉和我花了好些时间推测.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge and I spend hours speculating.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.08,0:29:40.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,无论如何,我连想都不愿想到纽约.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Anyway, I don't even want to think about New York.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.41,0:29:42.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,准备好了吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Are you ready ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.00,0:29:47.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 冰啤酒.谢谢,老爸.    - 好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Cold beer. Thank you, Dad.  - Okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.53,0:29:49.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,从这儿开始抄.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Copy out from here.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.01,0:29:54.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你把这个一起带到欧洲来了?     - 你打算写吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- You bring this with you to Europe ? - You gonna write something ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.38,0:29:57.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,我注意到你带来了莎士比亚却没带来衣服.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I love the fact that you brought Shakespeare with you but no clothes.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.68,0:30:01.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,厄玛琳达告诉我你每天晚上都洗同一件衬衫，是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ermalinda says you wash out the same shirt every night. Is that true ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.18,0:30:03.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有.我的衬衫不止一件.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No. I have more than one shirt.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.27,0:30:05.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,她会帮你洗的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}She can do that for you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.44,0:30:08.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过,你也可以穿我的衣服.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Anyway, just wear some of my stuff.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.15,0:30:10.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,随便穿.大多都有些旧了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Wear anything you want. Most of it's ancient.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.78,0:30:14.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在签个名.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Now your signature.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.70,0:30:20.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是这样迪克.你的签名.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Not Dickie.Your signature.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.55,0:30:34.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,不带眼镜,你还挺帅的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Without the glasses,you're not even ugly.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.05,0:30:39.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不需要眼镜，因为我从来不看书\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't need them because I never read.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.64,0:30:42.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我看起来怎么样?   -像克拉克-肯特.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- How do I look ?  - Like Clark Kent.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.56,0:30:48.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,-现在是超人了.   -超人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Now Superman.  - Superman.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.40,0:30:55.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,-好.    -我知道了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Okay.  - I know.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.90,0:31:00.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,这像个小孩子写的.看见没有, 这个 "S"和"T"?看起来很脆弱.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's like a kid's. See this, the "S" and the "T" ? Fine, vulnerable.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.83,0:31:03.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,那是痛苦.那是不为人知的痛苦.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That's pain.That's secret pain.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.91,0:31:06.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,好啊,那一定是个隐藏的非常深的秘密,连我自己都不知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, that must be a very deep secret, 'cause I don't know about it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.92,0:31:10.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯.没有什么能比你的笔迹更能泄漏你心底的秘密.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hmm. There's nothing more naked than your handwriting.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.24,0:31:13.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有字是挨着线的，看到吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}See how nothing's quite touching the line ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.09,0:31:17.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,-那是空虚.  -呃, 我们都知道就是这样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- That's vanity. - Well, we certainly know that's true.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.06,0:31:25.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,你有兄弟吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Dickie ]Do you have any brothers ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.68,0:31:28.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.12,0:31:30.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有兄弟,没有姐妹.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No brothers,no sisters.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.69,0:31:35.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,我也一样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Me neither.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.23,0:31:37.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.78,0:31:37.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉也一样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Nor does Marge.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.03,0:31:41.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,都是独子.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}All only children.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.79,0:31:49.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What does that mean ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.13,0:31:54.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,意味着我们从未和人共用一个浴池.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Means we've never shared a bath.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:32:01.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,我很冷.我能进来吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I'm cold.Can I get in ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.43,0:32:09.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,不能.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.61,0:32:15.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不是说和你一起.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I didn't mean with you in it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.15,0:32:22.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,好吧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.82,0:32:26.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,进来吧.我也该去修修边幅了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Get in. I'm like a prune anyway.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.57,0:32:51.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是我.不过是年代久远罢了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It is me.It's an old picture.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.11,0:32:54.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,每次都是这样! "是你吗?看起来不像你."\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Every time ! "Is it you ?It doesn't look like you."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.44,0:32:56.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,天!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}God !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.36,0:32:59.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,信..格林立夫写给瑞普雷的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Letters..Greenleaf and for Ripley.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.23,0:33:02.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢.弗朗. "我想念你.你什么时候回来?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ooh. Fran. "I miss you.When are you coming home ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.23,0:33:04.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,别告诉我你在那儿过得有多开心.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Stop telling me what an incredible time you're having.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.87,0:33:06.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,-或是你又多爱迪克.   -哇噢!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- How much you love Dickie. - Whoo !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.04,0:33:10.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,爱玛吉和蒙吉."\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And Marge and Mongibello."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.24,0:33:12.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,这封信，我认为是你父亲写的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And this one, I think, is from your father.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.33,0:33:16.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Dickie Vocalizing: Jazz]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.04,0:33:21.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,-让我看看.他说了些什么?  -他开始不耐烦了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Let me see it. What does he say ? - He's getting impatient.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.17,0:33:25.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,他想让我保证你能在感恩节前赶回去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He wants me to reassure him that you're going to be home by Thanksgiving.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.68,0:33:28.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,你得买件新外套了，真的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You've got to get a new jacket. Really.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.56,0:33:30.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,老穿一件衣服，你一定觉得很厌烦了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You must be sick of wearing the same clothes.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.85,0:33:33.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不能.我不能老花你父亲的钱.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I can't. I can't keep spending your father's money.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.90,0:33:36.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢你的责任感.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I love how responsible you are.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.90,0:33:40.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,我爸爸会让你做个首席会计之类的工作.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}My dad should make you chief accountant or something.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.07,0:33:43.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,或者等我接管的时候, 我想那是不可能发生了,我聘你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Or when I take over,which is never, I will.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.11,0:33:46.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,好的. 当你接管的时候,反正遥遥无期,我接受.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Okay. When you take over,which is never, I'll accept.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.91,0:33:49.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,让我给你买件外套. 当我们一起去罗马的时候,那儿有个极好的地方...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Let me buy you a jacket. When we get to Rome, there's a great place...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.12,0:33:52.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,-巴蒂斯多尼.   -巴蒂斯多尼.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Battistoni.  - Battistoni.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.82,0:33:56.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.58,0:33:59.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,罗马,我们带汤姆去罗马\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Roma, we're taking Tom to Roma{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.80,0:34:03.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们一起去罗马\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We’re going to a-Roma{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.59,0:34:06.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering in Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.97,0:34:13.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,早上好.漂亮的毛衣.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Buongiorno.Nice sweater.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.85,0:34:15.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们应该到哪儿雇辆马车去广场?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Where do we get a carrozza for the Forum ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.98,0:34:18.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我们能雇他们吗?   -放松点.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Can we just hire any of them ? - Relax.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.74,0:34:20.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,放松点!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Relax !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.16,0:34:20.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.03,0:34:23.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,只是今天一天要做的事情太多了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It’s just there's so much to do in a single day.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.90,0:34:27.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,最重要的事是我们该去哪儿吃饭.我希望弗雷迪已经订好了位子.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The most important question is where to eat. I hope Freddie made a reservation.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.95,0:34:29.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,费雷迪?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Freddie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.95,0:34:33.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,费雷迪.费雷迪·迈尔斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Freddie.Freddie Miles.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.89,0:34:35.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,是费雷迪组织的科尔蒂纳滑雪游.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Freddie's organizing the Cortina skiing trip.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.71,0:34:37.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.50,0:34:40.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢,他来了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, here he is.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.12,0:34:42.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Tires Screech ]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.51,0:34:45.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,-弗朗西斯科!   -你好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Frederico ! - Comestai ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.79,0:34:48.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Italian ]\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.17,0:34:54.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,天,你是不是看到每个女人都想上一次?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, God, don't you want to fuck every woman you see just once ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.81,0:34:58.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 就一次?   - 当然.就一次.你好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Only once ?  - Absolutely. Once. Ciao.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.06,0:35:00.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,-汤姆·瑞普雷,弗雷迪·迈尔斯.  -汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Tom Ripley, Freddie Miles. - Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.29,0:35:05.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,我是指,嗨,如果我这也叫晚,想想看她老公会怎么说.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I mean, hey, if I'm late,think what her husband's saying.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.38,0:35:07.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你看起来棒极了.   -和往常一样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- You look gorgeous. - As always.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.07,0:35:10.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么,吃饭.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So, mangiare.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.08,0:35:13.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,好. 我在法布里兹奥订了张桌子.汤米.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Si. I got us a table outside at Fabrizio's. Tommy.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.50,0:35:15.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,太棒了.我告诉你,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Dickie]Outstanding. I tell you,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.50,0:35:18.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我快被蒙吉那个小地方给困死了.  -我知道，我去过那儿.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I'm so cabin-crazy with Mongi. - I know. I was there.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.37,0:35:20.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Jazz]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.85,0:35:36.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,看,汤姆,我们得去一个俱乐部见见弗雷迪的一群朋友.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Look, Tom, we got to go to a club and meet some friends of Freddie’s.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.06,0:35:40.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想去游玩，最好现在就去叫辆车。\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The best thing is, if you want to be a tourist, grab a cab now,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.52,0:35:43.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,我会和你在火车站碰头.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and I'll meet you at the railway station.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.28,0:35:45.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,哪家俱乐部?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What club ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.86,0:35:50.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷迪和滑雪团一些人安排的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Freddie's arranged it with some of the skiing crowd.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.87,0:35:54.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,你想来就来吧，不过我以为你想去观光.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Come if you want, but I thought you wanted to go sightseeing.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.45,0:35:57.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,我是想,也许还会去买件外套，你说过的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I do, and then maybe get the jacket and what have you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.24,0:35:59.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克!你得来听听这个.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dick !You gotta hear this.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.75,0:36:03.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,听着,先穿我的，等我们回来再说.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Listen, just take one of mine when we get back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.71,0:36:06.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,别担心\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Don't worry about it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.59,0:36:10.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,好吧!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Come on !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.26,0:36:22.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,再见.玩得开心点,好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ciao.Have fun, okay ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.86,0:36:33.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Knocking]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.41,0:36:38.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,你说过要确定你不会错过火车，8：00发车.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You said to make sure you didn't miss the train. Leaves at 8:00.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.91,0:36:40.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Snickers ]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.92,0:36:43.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,玩得开心点.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Have a good time.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.08,0:36:44.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,再见,汤米.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}See ya, Tommy.{\c}
