Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.14,0:45:28.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我不知道，你干吗问我?  -他们是在指责他吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I don't know. Why are you asking me ? - Are they blaming him ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.78,0:45:31.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么叫一辆救护车得花一个小时?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}How can it take an hour to find an ambulance ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.03,0:45:34.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,她早就死了,亲爱的,不是吗?所以我想...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}She was already dead, darling,wasn't she ? So I suppose...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.62,0:45:39.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道为什么人们说这个国家是个文明古国.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know why people say this country is civilized.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.47,0:45:42.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 迪克!  - 根本就不是.根本就是个原始社会.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Dickie ! - It isn't. It's fucking primitive.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.96,0:45:46.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,我去看看到底是怎么回事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'll go see what's the matter.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.42,0:45:48.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,我去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'll go.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.13,0:45:55.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Saxophone]
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.94,0:46:07.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你为什么伤心.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Tom]I know why you’re upset.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.61,0:46:12.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道希尔维那,迪克.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know about Silvana, Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.86,0:46:16.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你和希尔维那之间的关系.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know about you and Silvana.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.08,0:46:19.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们怎么了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What about us ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.71,0:46:26.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,你不需要来收拾!不需要!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You don't have to clean up ! Really !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.97,0:46:36.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,-比如什么?   -算了吧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Like what ? - Forget it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.85,0:46:41.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,她怀孕了.你知道吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}She was pregnant.Did you know that ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.85,0:46:48.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,希尔维那怀孕了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Silvana was pregnant.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.23,0:46:52.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道这在这种地方意味着什么吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Do you know what that means in a place like this ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.90,0:46:55.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,我已经准备好了接受指责.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm prepared to take the blame.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.91,0:46:59.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你说什么呢?   -你一直对我这么好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What are you talking about ? - You've been so good to me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.87,0:47:04.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,你就像是我从未有过的兄弟.我就像是你从未有过的兄弟\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're the brother I never had.I'm the brother you never had.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.66,0:47:07.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,我可以为你做任何事,迪克.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I would do anything for you, Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.71,0:47:11.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,她来求我帮助她.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}She came to me for help.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.88,0:47:14.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,她需要钱.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}She needed money.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.01,0:47:21.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,我没帮她.我没帮她.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I didn't help her.I didn't help her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.51,0:47:25.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在她自杀了，这全是我的错.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Now she’s drowned herself,and it's my fault.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.36,0:47:35.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不会说出去的...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm not going to say anything...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.38,0:47:38.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,包括玛吉，包括警察，任何人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}to Marge, to the police or anybody.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.36,0:47:41.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们俩人之间的秘密，迪克.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's a secret between us, Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.58,0:47:45.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,我会保守秘密的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I'll keep it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.08,0:47:49.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,"亲爱的汤姆.看到迪克在你去了之后...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Tom Reading] “Dear Tom.in view of the fact Dickie shows...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.71,0:47:54.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,并不比以前更想回家...如此这般，如此这般...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}no more signs of coming home than before you went...” blah, blah, blah...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.55,0:47:57.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.38,0:48:00.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,"我希望这次旅行给你带来了一定快乐...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}"I hope that the trip has afforded you some pleasure...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.09,0:48:03.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,虽然目标并没有达成.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}despite the failure of its main objective.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.39,0:48:07.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,你也无需认为还对我们负有任何义务."\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You no longer should consider yourself obligated to us in any way."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.94,0:48:09.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,不能怪他.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Can't blame him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.02,0:48:12.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,不会一直这样下去的,汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You could hardly expect this to go on forever, Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.33,0:48:14.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃, 你可以再写信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, you can write again.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.73,0:48:17.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,-特别是我们现在已经成兄弟了.   -我不能.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Especially now we're brothers. - I can't.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.74,0:48:19.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么能这么做,会很丢脸.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}How can l,in all decency.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.91,0:48:22.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,你自己说过.你在这里花的钱都是我父亲的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You said it yourself.It’s my dad's money you're spending.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.74,0:48:26.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们玩得很开心，不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We've had a great run though, haven't we ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.91,0:48:30.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃,我们还是要去威尼斯.我们可以按原计划去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, we'll still go to Venice.We could stick to that plan.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.92,0:48:33.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不这样认为,汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't think so, Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.09,0:48:35.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,你无法支付旅费,不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You can’t pay your own way, can you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.76,0:48:40.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们都该往前了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It’s time we all moved on.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.61,0:48:44.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,我受不了蒙吉.特别是现在,当一切都..\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm sick of Mongi.Especially now, with everything..{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.51,0:48:46.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,我真的很想搬去北方.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I really want to move to the north.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.56,0:48:49.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,我下星期要去圣雷默看看.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I need to check out San Remo next week.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.14,0:48:51.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,给游艇找个新地方.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Find somewhere new to keep the boat.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.26,0:48:54.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,当然，如果你能来就太好了,如果你和我一起去圣雷默.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It would be great, though, if you came with me to San Remo.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.73,0:48:58.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,哪儿有个很棒的爵士节.我们可以很体面地告别.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There's a great jazz festival.We could say good-bye in style.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.79,0:49:00.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得呢?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What do you think ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.95,0:49:03.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们最后的旅行!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Our last trip !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.29,0:49:11.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,当然.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Sure.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.82,0:49:49.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Speaking Italian]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.51,0:50:07.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,你干吗老那么扭你的脖子?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Why do you do that thing with your neck ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.85,0:50:09.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,怎么扭了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What thing ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.98,0:50:15.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,在火车上,你老是这么干.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}On trains, you always\N{\fnTahoma\fs14}{\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}do that thing.{\c}{\c}{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.40,0:50:22.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,阴森森的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Spooky.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.36,0:50:26.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,阴森森...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Spook... k.k..k.k..k.k..{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.23,0:50:29.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Imitating Jazz Percussion ]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.24,0:50:32.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,阴森森.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Spooky.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.88,0:50:32.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.24,0:50:34.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Cymbals]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.45,0:50:38.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Jazz ]
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.69,0:50:55.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.71,0:50:59.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不是告诉过你圣雷默很疯狂?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Didn't I tell you San Remo was crazy ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.07,0:51:01.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,这才像嘛!来啊!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}This is more like it !Come on !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.11,0:51:06.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Ends ]
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.75,0:51:14.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Grazie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.33,0:51:17.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,敬蒙吉，敬我生命中最快乐的时光.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}To Mongibello and the happiest days of my life.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.58,0:51:20.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,敬蒙吉,你今晚很开心.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}To Mongi.You're cheerful tonight.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.25,0:51:22.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,我突然很高兴快回去了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm suddenly quite happy to be going back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.96,0:51:22.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.76,0:51:25.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,在普林斯顿时我认识你吗，汤姆?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Did I know you at Princeton, Tom ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.59,0:51:29.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不觉得我认识你,不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't think I did,did I ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.04,0:51:31.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,-为什么突然一下问起这个?  -没什么.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Why are you asking all of a sudden ? - No reason.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.60,0:51:35.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,也许是因为你要离开了,我猜.我不认为你是打那儿毕业的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Because you're leaving, I guess.I don't think you were there.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.26,0:51:39.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 为什么?  - 我是在恭维你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Why ? - I mean it as a compliment.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.48,0:51:41.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,你的品位很高.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You've got such great taste.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.48,0:51:45.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,普林斯顿那帮俗人什么都尝试所以没品.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Most of the thugs at Princeton had tasted everything and had no taste.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.74,0:51:50.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,我经常这样说,"美国奶油:又厚又油."\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I used to say,"the cream of America: rich and thick."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.83,0:51:52.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷迪就是一个典型.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Freddie's the perfect example.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.99,0:51:55.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,那我就当恭维来听了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Then I'll take it as a compliment.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.66,0:51:57.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,我就知道!我就知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I knew it !I knew it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.71,0:52:00.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉和我打了个赌.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge and I had a bet.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.93,0:52:10.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是否真喜欢爵士,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Do you even like jazz,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.89,0:52:13.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,或者只是为了迎合我?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}or was that for my benefit ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.26,0:52:16.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我当然喜欢.  -噢,太好了!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I've gotten to like it.  - Oh, yes !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.60,0:52:20.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢你和你所有的生活方式.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I’ve gotten to like everything about the way you live.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.56,0:52:22.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,这事关爱.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's one big love affair.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.94,0:52:27.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你知道我以前在纽约的生活..\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}If you knew my life back home in New York..{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.15,0:52:29.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想放弃吹萨克斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm thinkin' of givin' up the sax.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.82,0:52:31.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得做鼓手怎么样?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What do you think about the drums ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.53,0:52:34.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,-什么?   -太酷了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What ? - So cool.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.83,0:52:37.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,我明天打算租艘船,四处看看.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm gonna rent a boat tomorrow,take a look around.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.79,0:52:41.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,我当初就是这么找到蒙吉的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}This is how I found my place in Mongi.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.42,0:52:44.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,租艘船...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Took a boat out...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.55,0:52:46.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,绕着海岸行驶,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}around the bay,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.59,0:52:49.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,遇到第一个我喜欢的,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}first thing I liked,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.25,0:52:51.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,我就要它.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I got it.{\c}
