Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.74,1:02:18.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,见鬼!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Goddamn it !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.50,1:02:21.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Tom ]Are you okay?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.57,1:02:35.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是迪克夹在香水盒里的一封信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There was a letter from Dickie in with my perfume.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.39,1:02:41.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道这次并不是多呆几天.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You realize it's more than just a few days.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.14,1:02:45.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,他想着要搬到罗马去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He's thinking of moving to Rome.[ Sniffles ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.31,1:02:47.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,事实上是,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The thing is,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.69,1:02:50.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,他离开前一天的晚上,我们...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}the night before he left, we...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.44,1:02:53.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们商量要搬到一起住...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}we talked about moving together...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.23,1:02:57.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,北面的某个地方,我猜我...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}somewhere north,and I suppose I...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.95,1:03:02.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,是在结婚这件事上给了他太多的压力.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}put some pressure on him about getting married.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.50,1:03:06.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,我只是...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I just...[ Sobs ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.38,1:03:11.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,只是我有可能把他吓走了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I just might have scared him off.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.34,1:03:19.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,当我们一起躺在床上...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There's a side to him...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.06,1:03:22.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,我望着他的侧面...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}when our heads are on the pillow...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.48,1:03:26.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道再没有人能像他这样温柔.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know no one else sees that's so tender.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.90,1:03:31.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想我该跟随你到罗马去问问他。\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I think I should come with you to Rome and confront him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.53,1:03:40.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,他讨厌被质问.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He hates being confronted.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.41,1:03:44.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,我认为你是对的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I think you’re right.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.32,1:03:55.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢.住店.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Grazie.Checking in.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.88,1:04:05.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,住店.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Checking in.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.88,1:04:11.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 瑞普雷先生?   - 对.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Signor Ripley ?  - It's me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.71,1:04:15.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Signor Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.35,1:04:17.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,当然是格林立夫先生.欢迎回来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Of course.Welcome back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.94,1:04:20.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Thank you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.50,1:04:40.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,喂?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Woman ] Pronto ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.60,1:04:43.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,是的, 我想打个电话给高道尼旅馆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yes, I'd like to telephone the Hotel Goldoni.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.62,1:04:47.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 好的, 先生. - 我找托马斯·瑞普雷.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Si, signor. - I want to speak to Thomas Ripley.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.89,1:04:50.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 瑞普雷? 知道了.  - 是的. 谢谢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Ripley ? Subito.  - Yes. Grazie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.82,1:05:04.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 喂.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Phone Buzzes] - Pronto.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.91,1:05:06.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生,瑞普雷先生不在.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Signor Greenleaf,Signor Ripley's not there.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.44,1:05:08.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 他不在?   - 不在, 先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- He's not there ?  - No, signor.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.08,1:05:10.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,好吧, 我留个言.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, I would like to leave a message.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.92,1:05:14.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 他不在那儿? 那我留言吧.   - 不在, 先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- He's not there ? I'll leave a message.  - No, signor.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.25,1:05:16.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 接到你的电话.  - 接到你的电话.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Got your call. - Got your call.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.42,1:05:18.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 今晚共餐... - 今晚共餐...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Dinner tonight... - Dinner tonight...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.42,1:05:19.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 似乎不错.     - 似乎不错.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- sounds fine. - sounds fine.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.43,1:05:22.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 瑞普雷. 瑞普雷.   - 瑞普雷.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Ripley. Ripley.   - Ripley.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.01,1:05:26.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 迪克·格林立夫.     - 迪克·格林立夫.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Dickie Greenleaf.  - [ Woman ] Dickie Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.60,1:05:29.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 是的. 格林立夫.   - 格林立夫.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Yes. Greenleaf.   - Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.65,1:05:31.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,在格兰得旅馆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}At the Grand.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.86,1:05:35.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想在这个钱包上加点装饰.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Tom] And I’d like to have this wallet embossed.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.36,1:05:37.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道这个词用英文怎么说.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know the word in Italian.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.36,1:05:39.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,装饰一下. 当然可以,格林立夫先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Embossed. Of course,Signor Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.45,1:05:41.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Thank you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.41,1:05:48.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克!我是....\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie !It's...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.96,1:05:55.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 天啊.     - 梅瑞迪斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Oh, my gosh.  - Meredith.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.08,1:05:56.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你好!   - 你好. 请进. 请进.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Ciao !  - Ciao. Come in. Come in.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.97,1:05:59.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过你会和那些美国佬一起去滑雪，对吧?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But you're going skiing with those Yankees, aren't you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.68,1:06:03.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么?   - 圣诞节. 去科尔蒂纳滑雪.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What ?  - At Christmas. To Cortina.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.44,1:06:05.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 和弗雷迪·迈尔斯.   - 你是怎么知道的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- With Freddie Miles. - How did you know that ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.48,1:06:09.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢! 人人都认识弗雷迪·迈尔斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh ! Everybody knows Freddie Miles.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.68,1:06:14.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷迪在罗马?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Is Freddie in Rome ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.70,1:06:16.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 现在?   - 对.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Now ?   - Yeah.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.28,1:06:18.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢, 我可不这样想.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, I don't think so.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.70,1:06:23.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过我...不过我见过他,当然, 我们还聊了几句.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But l...But I've met him,of course, and we've chatted.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.38,1:06:26.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,而且我还知道你...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I know about you...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.98,1:06:29.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,和玛吉两人在蒙吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and Marge in Mongi.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.55,1:06:32.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,你还真是只靠不住的小老鼠啊.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What an unreliable rat you are.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.85,1:06:35.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,当然, 弗雷迪说你是只小老鼠.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, Freddie said you were a rat.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.51,1:06:37.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在我想到了,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I thought to myself,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.52,1:06:40.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,"为什么他旅行时以'R'作为姓名首字母"\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}"Ah, now I know why\N{\fnTahoma\fs14}{\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}he travels under 'R."'{\c}{\c}{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.73,1:06:43.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,我离开了玛吉,梅瑞迪斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I've left Marge,Meredith.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.35,1:06:45.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,离开了蒙吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And Mongi.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.44,1:06:49.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 所以现在这只老鼠在罗马了.   - 噢，太遗憾了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- So the rat's here in Rome.  - Oh, I'm sorry.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.78,1:06:51.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢, 别觉得遗憾, 别.我从未这样开心过。\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, don't be sorry, no.I've never been happier.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.99,1:06:55.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,我...我觉得自己好像被赋予了新生命.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I...I feel like I've been handed a new life.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.37,1:07:00.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,事实是如果你一生都很富有,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The truth is that if you’ve had money your entire life,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.34,1:07:03.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,你要么就像我们这样蔑视金钱...对吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}either you despise it,which we do...agreed ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.71,1:07:06.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,你也只有在和其它那些富有又同样蔑视金钱的人一起时...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're only truly comfortable around other people...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.72,1:07:08.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,才会真正感觉舒服.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}who have it and despise it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.89,1:07:10.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.31,1:07:14.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,我还从来没向任何人坦白过这一点.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I've never admitted that to anyone.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.58,1:07:20.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering in Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.49,1:07:24.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为我的朋友格林立夫先生,格林立夫和我,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Meredith] Because my friend Mr. Greenleaf, Signor Greenleaf and I,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.82,1:07:26.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,打算花钱搞个小狂欢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}are on a little spending spree.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.33,1:07:29.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 明白了.   - 我们的行为不太检点.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Man] I see.  - We're behaving very badly.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.87,1:07:34.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢, 我喜欢意大利的纸币. 色调很暗.不会让我觉得有罪恶感.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, I love Italian money. So dark.Doesn't make you feel guilty.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.42,1:07:37.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢...谢.    - 谢谢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Gr-r-razie. - Thank you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.93,1:07:50.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不想要太多大钞.没人愿意找零.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't want too many large bills.No one will change them.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.52,1:07:52.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,完全没问题,格林立夫先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tutto bene,Signor Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.24,1:07:58.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Counting in Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.95,1:08:02.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Italian]
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.46,1:08:12.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我真的很喜欢这一件.  - 我想把它也买下来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I really like this too. - I think I'm having that too.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.18,1:08:13.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.47,1:08:20.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 明天.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Tomorrow.- [ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.77,1:08:28.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 再见.   - 再见. 噢!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Arrivederci.  - Arrivederci. Oops !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.48,1:08:31.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 再见.  - 再见.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Ciao.  - Ciao.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.91,1:08:41.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你是个爵士迷,不过你就一定恨歌剧吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know you're a jazz fiend, but do you absolutely hate the opera ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.54,1:08:47.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,我一直想...我一直想...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I've...I've...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.80,1:08:51.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,解决掉我的几张门票.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}been trying to give my tickets away.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.63,1:08:55.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,明天的. 不过如果你愿意被硬拖着去的话...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's tomorrow. But if you were prepared to be dragged...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.28,1:08:59.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,你可以拉我去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You could drag me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.60,1:09:06.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Opera: Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.44,1:09:56.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Shot Fires]
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.78,1:09:58.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Body Thuds]
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.16,1:10:46.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Audience Applauding]
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.35,1:10:52.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,费奥多·卡利亚宾.全是俄国男中音.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Feodor Chaliapin.It's the whole Russian baritone.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.04,1:10:54.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢你今晚邀请我来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Thank you so much for inviting me tonight.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.90,1:10:58.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,你受的了?我们听说你是弗雷迪的朋友.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Can you bear it ?We hear you are a friend of Freddie's.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.83,1:11:02.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,他在胸前纹了"我恨歌剧"几个字.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He has "I hate opera" tattooed on his chest.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.08,1:11:04.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷迪胸前足够刻上整个歌剧剧本了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There's room for a whole libretto on Freddie's chest.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.67,1:11:09.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,我确信我们见过面.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm sure we've met before.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.09,1:11:13.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,我确信我们见过面.你觉得呢, 泰德?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was sure we'd met before.Weren't you, Ted ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.09,1:11:15.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克是赫伯特·格林立夫的儿子.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dick is Herbert Greenleaf's boy.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.18,1:11:16.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我知道.   - 对, 我想我们见过面.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I know.   - Yes, I think we have.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.85,1:11:21.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,一分钟前你们还是孩子,  一眨眼功夫连纹身都纹上了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}One minute you people are children,and the next you're getting tattooed.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.90,1:11:26.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 干杯.   - 干杯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Cheers.  - Cheers.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.57,1:11:29.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,干杯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Cheers.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.83,1:11:36.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 请让一下.   - 请.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Excuse me.  - Prego.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.65,1:11:38.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢!对不起.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh !Excuse me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.75,1:11:41.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你好.   - 你好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Hello.  - Hello.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.50,1:11:45.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 汤姆!   - 玛吉!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Tom !   - Marge !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.05,1:11:48.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好吗?你来罗马干什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}How are you ?What are you doing in Rome ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.72,1:11:51.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 他在这儿吗? 你是和迪克一起的吗?  - 不. 嗯, 不是.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Is he here ? Are you with Dickie ? - No. Um, no.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.49,1:11:55.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯, 你好.嗯, 我是汤姆·瑞普雷.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um, hello.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14}{\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um, I'm Tom Ripley.{\c}{\c}{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.06,1:11:57.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,彼得·史密斯·金斯利.我从玛吉和迪克那儿听说过不少你的事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Peter Smith-Kingsley. I've heard all about you from Marge and Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.06,1:12:00.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 果然如此.  - 没..没戴眼镜.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Ditto.   - No..No glasses.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.06,1:12:03.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么, 你把他藏哪儿了?他真是不可理喻, 不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So, where are you hiding him ?He's impossible, isn't he ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.98,1:12:06.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,他真不在这?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Is he really not here ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.11,1:12:08.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉, 你知道迪克在胸前刻着"我恨歌剧" 几个字.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, you know Dickie has"I hate opera" tattooed on his chest.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.91,1:12:12.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我以为你们去了威尼斯.  - 是呀, 后来怎么样了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I thought you were going to Venice.  - Yes, what happened with that ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.04,1:12:13.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,我听说你一心想来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I heard you were desperate to come.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.04,1:12:16.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,我还期盼着能带你去划船.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was rather looking forward to rowing you around.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.48,1:12:20.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 是啊，我是很想来着.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Bell Ringing] - I am. I really am.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.88,1:12:23.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,我一直在旅行,但好像就是到不了那么北的地方.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I've been traveling, and I just can't seem to get that far north.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.18,1:12:25.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,好吧, 你得快点,否则我们都得沉了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, you should hurry,before we sink.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.09,1:12:28.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,这样吧, 我给你我的电话号码.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Look, let me give you the telephone number.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.22,1:12:32.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,看那儿. 噢, 看.那不是梅瑞迪斯吗.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There. Oh, look.There's Meredith.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.38,1:12:35.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,梅瑞迪斯. 她姓什么来着,玛吉? 那些开纺织厂的人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Meredith. What's her name,Marge ? The textile people.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.56,1:12:39.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯, 想想. 我们一些人还在她家度过圣诞.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um, come on. Some of us spent Christmas at her house.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.11,1:12:41.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不认识她.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.95,1:12:46.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,他从未打过电话.连信都很少写.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He hasn't called.He's hardly written.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.79,1:12:48.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,就是写点神秘小纸条,你知道吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Just these cryptic notes, you know ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.45,1:12:50.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你不能就这样甩了别人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- You don't just dump people. - [Bell Rings]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.12,1:12:53.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,这样吧, 我们是呆会见,或者你是和其它人一起来的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Look, will we see you later,or are you with people ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.79,1:12:57.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗯, 呆会不行.  - 这样吧, 明天怎么样?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Uh, I can't later. - Well, how about tomorrow ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.48,1:12:59.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,好啊, 嗯,早上怎么样?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yes, uh,maybe in the morning ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.40,1:13:03.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道斯帕格纳广场边的蒂内利咖啡店吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Do you know Cafe Dinelli at the Piazza di Spagna ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.36,1:13:06.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我知道那广场. 几点?   - 10:30?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I know the Piazza. What time ?  - 10:30 ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.18,1:13:08.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们会准时到的.   - 好的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- We'll be there.   - Okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.48,1:13:10.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,那明天见, 玛吉?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So I'll see you in the morning, Marge ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.61,1:13:13.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,10.:30   很高兴认识你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}10.:30   Very nice to meet you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.74,1:13:15.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,我也一样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Peter]And you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.66,1:13:20.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,来吧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Come on.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.62,1:13:24.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,来吧.让我们进去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Come on.Let's go back in.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.46,1:13:34.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白汤姆为什么还在罗马.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't understand why Tom's still in Rome.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.13,1:13:38.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们走吧.   - 我还以为你很喜欢歌剧呢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Whispering ] Let's go. - I thought you were enjoying yourself.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.97,1:13:40.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,让我们乘马车看看月亮.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Let's take a carrozza and look at the moon.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.66,1:13:43.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,你疯了吗?外面冷极了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Are you crazy ?It's freezing out there.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.35,1:13:45.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,来吧. 我得和你谈谈.就我们俩.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Come on. I need to talk to you.Just the two of us.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.47,1:13:47.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,好吧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Meredith]Okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.11,1:13:53.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,请别担心.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Meredith ]Don't worry, please.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.70,1:13:56.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,别担心.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Don't worry.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.62,1:14:00.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,你真的很善解人意. 我...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're such a palto understand. I...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.79,1:14:03.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,就好像玛吉无时无刻不在这儿.当我望着你的脸庞,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's like Marge is here right now. I look at you,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.70,1:14:05.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,就看到了她的脸.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and I see her face.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.17,1:14:08.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,我就是不能...不管我对你的感觉到底如何...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I can't... No matter what I'm feeling towards you...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.41,1:14:13.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,不用解释. 我完全...理解. 当...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No. I absolutely...understand. Of c...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.49,1:14:16.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,要不然, 你会抗拒我的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Otherwise, you'd be fighting me off.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.02,1:14:18.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,打走你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Beating you away.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.65,1:15:00.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过我们明天能见面吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But will you meet me tomorrow ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.94,1:15:04.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,就是来个正式告别,你知道, 在白天,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Just to say good-bye properly,you know, in the daylight,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.88,1:15:06.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,不像现在这样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}so it's not just this.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.49,1:15:10.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,当然. 梅瑞迪斯,很抱歉.我当然会去见你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Of course. Meredith, I'm sorry.Of course I'll meet you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.04,1:15:14.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,你永远都应该把痛苦留给白天.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You should always save pain for daylight.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.63,1:15:17.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,不如我们明天早上一起去蒂内利喝咖啡?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Why don't we have coffee in the morning at Dinelli's ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.01,1:15:20.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢, 就在西班牙阶梯旁边.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Uh, by the Spanish Steps.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.43,1:15:23.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,完全正确. 10:30 ?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Exactly. 10:30 ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.81,1:15:27.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 10:15.  - 好的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- 10:15.  - Okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.48,1:15:29.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,好的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.04,1:15:41.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Bell Tolling]
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.79,1:15:46.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Tolling Continues]
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.76,1:15:58.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.24,1:16:18.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering, indistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.77,1:16:24.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢.   - 彼得?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Peter ] Grazie.  - Peter ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.45,1:16:26.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好.我是梅瑞迪斯·罗吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hello.It's Meredith Logue.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.88,1:16:30.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,当然是你.梅瑞迪斯, 你好. 对不起.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Peter] Of course it is.Meredith, hello. Sorry.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.55,1:16:32.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我还没睡醒呢. 你好吗?   - 你好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I was half asleep. How are you ?  - How are you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.76,1:16:35.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是玛吉·舍伍德,梅瑞迪斯·罗吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}This is Marge Sherwood.Meredith Logue.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.18,1:16:38.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}How do you do ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.22,1:16:41.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,来和我们坐一起吧?我们正在等个朋友.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Do join us, won’t you ?We’re just waiting for a friend.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.69,1:16:44.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,我...不了, 其实.我想这有些...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I...I won't, actually.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14}{\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I think there's...{\c}{\c}{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.53,1:16:47.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们昨天在歌剧院见过对吗?  - 嗯...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Did we see you at the opera last night ? - Uh...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.19,1:16:49.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,你们是在等迪克?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Are you waiting for Dickie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.99,1:16:54.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克? 你...你...你认识迪克?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie ? Do you...Do you...Do you know Dickie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.20,1:16:58.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是在歌剧院.噢, 难怪...是的, 我在那儿.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You were at the opera.Oh, that explains...Yes, I was there.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.00,1:17:00.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,我和迪克一起去的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was there with Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.05,1:17:04.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,我就知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Exhales ]I knew it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.88,1:17:07.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,我告诉过你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I told you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.18,1:17:13.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉, 我和你不熟,所以我也没权利对你说什么...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, I don't know you,so I've got no right to...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.77,1:17:16.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克爱你.他就是...这样说吧...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie loves you.He's...Well...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.06,1:17:20.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想你会发现他现正赶着去找你呢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I think you’ll find he's on his way home to you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.40,1:17:24.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,好吧, 你是怎么..怎么..怎么知道这些的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Sighs ] Well, how..how..how would you know that ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.57,1:17:28.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,他... 告诉了我一切.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He... told me everything.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.49,1:17:33.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢不, 我本应该在15分钟前和他见面的,那么, 嗯,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, I was supposed to meet him 15 minutes ago, so, uh,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.21,1:17:35.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想我得走了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm gonna go now,I think.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.92,1:17:40.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,天, 除非他是计划好了要让我们见面.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}God, unless he meant us to meet.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.09,1:17:42.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,那就有点太残酷了,不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That’d be a little cruel,wouldn't it ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.25,1:17:44.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,不, 不是, 我们在等其它朋友.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, no, we're meeting another friend.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.80,1:17:47.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 汤姆·瑞普雷.   - 你认识过汤姆·瑞普雷?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Tom Ripley.   - Do you know Tom Ripley ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.72,1:17:52.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,不, 不认识. 我当然听说过他,不过还没见过面, 没见过.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, no. I've heard about him,of course, but I didn't meet him, no.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.61,1:17:55.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我不要了. 不要了, 谢谢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Italian]- Not for me. No, grazie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.45,1:18:04.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,希望我没把事情搞复杂了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hope I didn't complicate matters.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.26,1:18:08.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,天, 没什么,没发生过任何过分的事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}God, nothing, nothing...untoward happened.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.83,1:18:13.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有, 没有任何事能阻止他回到你身边,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, there is nothing to prevent you from welcoming him back,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.13,1:18:16.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,能阻止他和你结婚.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}from marrying him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.64,1:18:23.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,再见.我很高兴又认识了一位新朋友.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Good-bye.I'm happy to put a face to a name.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.43,1:18:25.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,再见, 彼得.别，请别站起来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Good-bye, Peter.Please, don't get up.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.46,1:18:49.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在我完全不知所措了.你觉得他会回来吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Marge ] Now I don't know what to think. Do you think he's coming back ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.17,1:18:54.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,对不起. 对不起.得更新我的档案.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Sorry. Sorry.Had to renew my papers.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.49,1:18:56.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们总能把只要盖一个章就能解决的事搞得很复杂。\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Never one stamp when they can make you line up for three.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.39,1:18:58.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你们等了很久吗?   - 没有.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Have you been waiting long ? - Not at all.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.27,1:19:01.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 早上好, 汤姆.   - 早上好. 对不起.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Morning, Tom.   - Hi. Sorry.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.06,1:19:03.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗? 你看上去像撞了鬼一样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You okay ? You look like you’ve seen a ghost.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.46,1:19:05.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克昨天晚上也在歌剧院.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie was at the opera last night.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.86,1:19:10.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不信. 呃...野马也不能把他拽到那儿去...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't believe that. Uh...Wild horses couldn't drag Dickie...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.14,1:19:12.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,他和其它人一起去的, 你知道,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Laughs ] Well, he was there with someone, you know,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.61,1:19:14.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想她一定是硬拉他去的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}so I suppose she must have dragged him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.49,1:19:17.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,这不公平.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's not fair.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.08,1:19:21.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想我得回蒙吉了.迪克应该是已经回家了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I think I'm going back to Mongi.I think Dickie's coming home.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.22,1:19:23.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,是吗? 我...那简直是太好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Really ? I...Well,that’s just swell.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.05,1:19:26.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,不, 你知道, 你总是比我先知. 太好了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, you know, you'reway ahead of me. Great.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.76,1:19:29.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,我听到那席话时还觉得挺感动...对不起.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That was rather moving when I heard...I'm sorry.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.12,1:19:31.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,梅瑞迪斯是我昨晚在歌剧院看到的那个美国女孩.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Meredith is the American girl I saw at the opera last night.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.46,1:19:35.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 她了解迪克一些事.   - 哦, 上帝啊.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- She’s been seeing something of Dickie. - Oh, my God.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.93,1:19:38.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是重点在于,迪克...我们都知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But the point is,Dickie...and we all know this.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.98,1:19:42.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克爱玛吉.他也很想念她.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie loves Marge.And he misses her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.73,1:19:45.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,我有一种负疚感.玛吉并不了解,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I feel guilty.Marge doesn't understand this,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.57,1:19:48.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是每当迪克做错了事，我都会感觉愧疚.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}but whenever Dickie does something, I feel guilty.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.49,1:19:51.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,好像是心有灵犀一样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Chuckles ]As if that makes sense.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.46,1:19:55.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.88,1:19:57.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.15,1:20:20.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Choir Singing in Italian]
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.09,1:20:46.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Ends]
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.94,1:20:57.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Knocking At Door]
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.53,1:21:09.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,- [Knocking]\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Piano: Stops]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.22,1:21:16.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Freddie]Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.55,1:21:21.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 迪克, 开门. 是我.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Knocking]- Dickie, come on. It's me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.69,1:21:25.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,费雷迪.让我进来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's Freddie.Let me in.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.65,1:21:29.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.87,1:21:37.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好, 费雷迪.是汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hello, Freddie.It's Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.75,1:21:41.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯, 迪克在哪儿?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um, where's Dickie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.75,1:21:43.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}How are you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.75,1:21:46.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,还不错. 呃, 是的, 谢谢.他出门了. 他去吃晚饭了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm good. Uh, yes, thank you.He's gone. He went to dinner.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.94,1:21:51.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 他在澳泰罗饭店. 你知道澳泰罗吗?   - 不, 不, 不.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- He's at Otello's. You know Otello's ?- No, no, no.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.66,1:21:54.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,我..我不认为他会在下午6:30用晚餐.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I..I don't think he's at dinner at 6:30 P.M.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.32,1:21:57.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你说他还吃午饭,也许我会相信你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}If you said he was still at lunch, maybe I'd believe you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.56,1:22:01.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?难以置信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You know ? [ Laughs ]Incredible.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.23,1:22:05.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,我是说,那家伙就这么，你知道，就这么一下子从地球上消失了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I mean, the guy just, you know,disappeared off the face of the earth.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.22,1:22:09.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想是吧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I guess.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.26,1:22:13.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,房东,就我所知...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The landlady,as far as I could tell...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.58,1:22:17.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,房东说他现在就在这儿.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The landlady said he was here right now.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.42,1:22:19.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,你搜吧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Search the place.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.75,1:22:23.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,我..我只是不明白...不明白迪克为什么要躲着你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I..I just don't... I don't know why you'd imagine that Dickie would hide from you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.43,1:22:25.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为他以前也躲过我.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Because he's been hiding from me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.30,1:22:31.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 圣诞节怎么搞的?  - 圣诞节怎么了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What happened at Christmas ?  - What about Christmas ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.23,1:22:35.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,他本该一起来滑雪的.我连个电报都没收到...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He was supposed to come skiing.I didn't get a cable...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.48,1:22:36.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,或是一个电话，一张便条，或是一个...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}or a call or a little note or a...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.73,1:22:41.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 老实说, 连个屁都没有.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Grunts ] - Frankly, a fart.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.42,1:22:43.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,他最近很沉迷于他的音乐.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, he's been very involved with his music.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.66,1:22:47.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯,我认为他的理论.. 是...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um, I think his theory... is...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.95,1:22:53.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,你先得把自己裹在茧里,呃,才能变成一只蝴蝶.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}that you have to go into a cocoon,uh, before you can be a butterfly.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.33,1:22:55.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,胡说八道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Which is horseshit.[ Mutters ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.25,1:22:58.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,你听过他吹这个?呃,他不会.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You hear him play this thing ?Well, he can't.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.59,1:23:03.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是怎么找到他的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}How did you find him ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.76,1:23:07.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是这么偏远的一所房子.要我给你倒杯酒吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's such an out-of-the-way apartment.Can I fixyou a drink ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.49,1:23:10.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,不, 谢谢了.美国快递.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, thanks.At the American Express.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.43,1:23:12.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Strikes Random Keys ]
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.23,1:23:15.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,开玩笑的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Some kid.[ Strikes Keys ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.16,1:23:24.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,你住这儿吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Are you living here ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.16,1:23:28.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,不, 不. 我只在这儿逗留几天.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, no. I'm staying here for a few days.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.96,1:23:32.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,-那...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- But...- [Strikes Keys]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.67,1:23:36.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是台新钢琴.也许不该在这儿...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's a new piano.Probably shouldn't...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.31,1:23:39.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Striking Keys ]
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.93,1:23:43.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 也许不该...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Probably shouldn't...- [Strikes Keys]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.48,1:23:50.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,这地方装修过?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Did this place come furnished ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.32,1:23:53.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,看起来完全不像迪克的风格, 呃...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It doesn't look like Dickie's, uh...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.57,1:23:56.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,太差劲了,不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's really horrible,isn't it ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.24,1:24:01.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,太, 呃, 太小资了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's so, uh, bourgeois.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.26,1:24:14.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢, 那是一个, 呃...你得..小心点.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, that's a, uh...You should..Watch that.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.17,1:24:16.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,不好意思...让我来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Excuse...Excuse me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.73,1:24:18.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,我来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Excuse me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.69,1:24:26.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,事实上, 唯一一样像迪克的...是你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}In fact, the only thing that looks like Dickie... is you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.53,1:24:28.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 不太像吧.  - 嗯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Hardly.  - Hmm.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.24,1:24:32.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,你做过头发?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Have you done something to your hair ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.03,1:24:33.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.20,1:24:35.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,你想说什么，弗雷迪?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Is there something you'd like to say, Freddie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.49,1:24:38.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么?   - 你想说什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What ?  - You have something you'd like to say ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.45,1:24:40.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想我正说着.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I think I'm saying it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.59,1:24:44.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些事不对劲.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Something’s going on.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.80,1:24:47.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,要么就是他改变了信仰,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Either he's converted to Christianity,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.85,1:24:50.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,要么就是发生了其它什么事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}or there's something else.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.22,1:24:54.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃, 我建议你还是自己去找迪克问清楚.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, I would suggest you ask Dickie that yourself.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.46,1:24:57.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,澳泰罗餐馆就在街道出去的路口处.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Otello's is on della Croce just off the Corso.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.45,1:25:00.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,就在街道出去的路口处?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Is it on della Croce just off the Corso ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.95,1:25:07.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,是呀. 你学得可真快，不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Sure. You're a quick study, aren’t you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.28,1:25:09.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,上次你连意大利语的手肘和屁股都分不清楚.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Last time you didn't know you ass from your elbow.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.49,1:25:11.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在你已经能为我指路了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Now you're giving me directions.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.79,1:25:15.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,这不公平. 你也许能分得清你的屁股和手肘.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That’s not fair. You probably do know your ass from your elbow.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.46,1:25:20.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们会再见面的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'll see you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.79,1:25:27.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Door Opens, Closes]
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.67,1:25:32.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.52,1:25:35.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是迪克·格林立夫. 托马斯·瑞普雷.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Freddie]No Dickie Greenleaf. Thomas Ripley.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.59,1:25:38.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,是.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Si.[Italian]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.83,1:25:45.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好, 迪克.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ciao, Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.29,1:25:52.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克不弹钢琴.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie doesn't play the piano.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.30,1:25:56.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,汤米.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Freddie]Tommy.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.30,1:25:58.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,汤米!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tommy!{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.30,1:26:00.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,汤米!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tommy!{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.83,1:26:04.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Freddie Groaning]
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.89,1:26:25.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Tom Grunting]
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.78,1:26:37.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Man And Woman Chattering]
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.77,1:26:42.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢!你可真逗.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh ! [ Laughs ]You're making me laugh.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.35,1:26:46.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,不. 你不过是喝多了.噢. 你不过是...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No. You’re just so drunk.Oh. You’re just...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.16,1:26:48.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,你还能怎么样呢，嗯?你该看看我其它的朋友都醉成什么样了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What can you do, eh ?You should see my other friends.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.90,1:26:51.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你还能做什么呢?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What canyon do ?- [ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.32,1:26:54.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,是呀.根本就是一头猪.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yes.Such a pig.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.92,1:26:57.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Laughs ]\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.12,1:27:03.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗨, 如果我这就算醉了的话,想想他老公会怎么说.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Imitating Freddie ] Hey, if I'm drunk,think what her husband's saying.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.81,1:27:53.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 打搅了.   - 迪克.格林立夫?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- La polizia. - Dickie Greenleaf?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.27,1:27:56.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 是的.   - 罗维利尼警探.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Yes.   - Inspector Roverini.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.36,1:27:58.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们能进来吗?   - 请吧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Can we come in ? - Please.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.12,1:28:08.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,这真是令人震惊，不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's a terrible shock,huh ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.75,1:28:12.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,迈尔斯先生昨天是几点钟走的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}W-What time did Signor Miles leave yesterday ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.29,1:28:16.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢, 嗯, 我不敢肯定. 我想是...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, um, I can't be certain exactly. I...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.37,1:28:18.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,8:00, 9:00.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}8:00, 9:00.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.17,1:28:20.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.18,1:28:25.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们都, 呃,喝了太多酒.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We'd both taken on, uh,far too many drinks.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.64,1:28:30.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过那时天已经很黑了，天当然已经很黑了，当我..当我搀他进他自己的车里.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But it was dark. It was certainly dark when I.. when I walked him to his car.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.32,1:28:33.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么他开车走了,那么,呃,你做了什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So he drove away,and, uh, you did what ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.32,1:28:36.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 上床睡觉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I went to bed.- [ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.39,1:28:42.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷迪很能喝，不过我才喝了两杯就不行了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Freddie's a big man, but I'm in trouble after a couple of drinks.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.34,1:28:44.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,我一直都很难受...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I've been suffering all...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.67,1:28:46.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,谁找到他的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Who found him ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.83,1:28:50.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,请你理解,我一定得请你..\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Italian ]You understand, I must ask you...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.30,1:28:52.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,留在罗马,格林立夫先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}to stay in Rome,Signor Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.13,1:28:56.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,好的,如果能有所帮助的话,当然.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yes, if it's gonna help,certainly.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.31,1:28:59.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,那么, 法医, 他得, 嗯...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So, the doctor, he has to make the, um...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.47,1:29:02.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Italian ]\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.81,1:29:06.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 验尸.  - 对, 就是这样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Postmortem. - Yeah, exactly.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.11,1:29:08.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是,你看,他的初步推论是...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But, you know,his first conclusion...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.86,1:29:13.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,迈尔斯先生是昨晚7：00以前被杀害的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}was that Signor Miles was killed not later than 7:00 yesterday evening.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.99,1:29:18.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃, 他在开车走之前当然不会已经死了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, he certainly wasn't dead when he drove away in his car.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.50,1:29:22.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,不会.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.48,1:29:23.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering ]
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.96,1:29:41.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.74,1:29:49.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,没事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Italian ]It's okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.33,1:29:51.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 真没事?   - 是, 是的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Okay ?   - Si, si.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.59,1:30:06.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 是他杀的弗雷迪?   - 玛吉.你什么时候来的?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Did he kill Freddie ?  - Marge. When did you get here ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.42,1:30:08.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我真相.是他杀的弗雷迪吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tell me the truth.Did he kill Freddie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.39,1:30:11.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,我发誓他没有.他当然不会这么做.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'd swear he didn't.Of course he didn't.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.10,1:30:16.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,我又来碰碰运气.等在这儿, 看着他.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I tried again.Waiting here, watching for him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.40,1:30:20.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,相反, 是你.每次我找迪克，找到的都是你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Instead, it's you.Whenever I look for Dickie, I find you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.91,1:30:24.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,你脸怎么了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What happened to your face ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.95,1:30:26.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克...迪克干的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie...Dickie did it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.95,1:30:29.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 迪克?   - 我的脸. 我们起了些争执.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Dickie ? - My face. There was an argument.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.49,1:30:32.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,我...我说了些,我不该说的，而我...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I...I said some things I shouldn't have said and I...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.04,1:30:35.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,是关于你.关于他如此恶劣地对待你, 对待我们每一个人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}About you. About the appalling way he's treating you, all of us.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.75,1:30:38.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,接下来我就发现他只朝我冲过来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And the next thing I know,he's launched himself at me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.13,1:30:40.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你上来吗?  - 什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Are you getting on ? - What ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.30,1:30:43.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,上来.我带你去见他.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Get on.I'll take you to him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.72,1:31:09.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.11,1:31:24.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Engine Stops ]
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.98,1:31:29.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 他住哪儿?  - 在前面，我们过了几个街区.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Where does he live ? - We passed it a few blocks back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.99,1:31:32.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,那有警察.在乔亚的宅第.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's where the police were.The Palazzo Gioia.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.70,1:31:37.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,看, 他们甚至不知道我在罗马,我不能牵累迪克.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Look, they don't even know I'm in Rome,and I'm not gonna incriminate Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.74,1:31:38.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,恩, 也许我该走了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, perhaps I shouldn't go either.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.87,1:31:43.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,不. 好吧,你想走就走吧,但是别对警官说看到过我.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No. Well, go if you want to, but just don't talk to the police about my face.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.26,1:31:46.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们知道他打了我和他的火爆脾气,那他就能攻击弗雷迪.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}If they know he hit me and his temper,then he could've hit Freddie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.70,1:31:47.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,呆会见.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'll catch up with you later.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.97,1:31:53.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Engine Starts ]
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.19,1:32:09.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Italian ]Signor Greenleaf !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.24,1:32:12.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,是格林立夫先生!快，快!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's Signor Greenleaf !Presto, presto !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.76,1:32:14.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting in Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.29,1:32:20.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,开门!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Open the door !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.29,1:32:21.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,快开门!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Open up !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.05,1:32:25.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我住这儿!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Italian ]- I live here !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.41,1:32:27.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Mr. Greenleaf !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.76,1:32:30.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们能上去吗?你不介意吧?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Can we go up ?Do you mind ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.06,1:32:33.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,当然.你脸怎么了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Of course.What happened to your face ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.73,1:32:37.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,我的电单车. 在被摄影师追赶的时候摔的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}My scooter. I fell off getting chased by photographers.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.40,1:32:41.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,电话, 媒体,我觉得..我觉得在被追捕.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The telephone, the press,I've been...I'm feeling hounded.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.61,1:32:43.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,你就不能别泄漏我的地址吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Do you think you could not give out my address ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.78,1:32:48.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,从未.有很多人要求，但我们都拒绝了,连你的未婚妻都没有告知.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Never.We've had many requests, and we say no, even to your fiancée.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.61,1:32:50.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,我真的不想见任何人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I really don't want to see anybody.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.24,1:32:53.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 包括你的未婚妻?   - 包括她.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Even your fiancée ?  - Even her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.07,1:32:56.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Man Speaking Italian]
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.38,1:33:00.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 那汤姆·瑞普雷呢?  - 汤姆·瑞普雷怎么了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What about Thomas Ripley ? - What about Tom Ripley ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.59,1:33:04.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,你和瑞普雷先生一起去了圣雷默.对吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You and Signor Ripley went to San Remo.Is that right ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.40,1:33:07.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,是的, 我们..我们去了圣雷默.那已经是几个月以前的事情了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yes, we..We went to San Remo.That was months ago.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.05,1:33:09.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,十一月, 我想是.是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}November, I thought.Was it ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.10,1:33:12.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你和汤姆说过吗?   - 十一月七日我记得.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Did you speak to Tom ? - November 7 is my information.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.73,1:33:15.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,我记不清确切日期了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't remember the exact date.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.26,1:33:19.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你上一次见到瑞普雷先生是什么时候?  - 几天前。\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- When did you last see Signor Ripley ? - A few days ago.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.03,1:33:23.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 他住你这儿吗?   - 没有.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Does he stay with you here ?  - No.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.70,1:33:26.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.65,1:33:30.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,大致是这样的.两天前,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Here is a pattern.Two days ago,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.49,1:33:34.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷迪·迈尔斯死了,嗯?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Freddie Miles is dead,hmm ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.72,1:33:37.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,他离开你的公寓,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He leaves your apartment,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.26,1:33:41.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,就被谋杀了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and he's murdered.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.10,1:33:46.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,昨天, 一条盛满石块的小船在圣雷默被发现.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yesterday, a little boat is found in San Remo full of rocks.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.43,1:33:51.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,船主告诉警局船是11月7日被盗的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And the owner tells the police it was stolen on November 7.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.23,1:33:53.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们看了旅店纪录...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We look at hotel records...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.82,1:33:56.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们发现...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and we see...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.70,1:33:59.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克·格林立夫在圣雷默.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie Greenleaf is staying in San Remo.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.95,1:34:03.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,船主记得是两个美国人租的船.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And then our boatman remembers two Americans taking a boat.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.79,1:34:06.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,这不是大概.纯属巧合.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That is not a pattern.That's a coincidence.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.07,1:34:08.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,在圣雷默有50家旅馆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There must be 50 hotels in San Remo.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.84,1:34:11.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,那天也许有100个人租了船.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There were probably a hundred people renting a boat that day.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.59,1:34:14.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,31人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Thirty-one people.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.18,1:34:16.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,31人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Thirty-one people.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.31,1:34:19.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,31人,是的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Thirty-one, yeah.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.83,1:34:21.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.50,1:34:24.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 玛吉·舍伍德.  - 这次是舍伍德小姐.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Marge Sherwood.  - That is Miss Sherwood now.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.83,1:34:34.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,让她进来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Let her in.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.91,1:34:38.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,让她进来.这又有能怎么样? 让她进来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Let her in.What's the difference ? Let her in.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.04,1:34:43.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,不! 事实上...事实上, 不.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No ! Actually...Actually, no.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.77,1:34:46.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,我会...我会很感激的...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I would...I would really appreciate it...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.46,1:34:49.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你等会再让舍伍德小姐进来的话.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}if you would ask Miss Sherwood to come back later.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.51,1:34:53.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.93,1:34:56.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Thank you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.45,1:35:00.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,我可以问一下吗..\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}May I ask you..{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.44,1:35:03.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你宁可对朋友说，却不愿对你的未婚妻说?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Why would you speak to your friend and not your fiancée ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.15,1:35:07.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃, 我..我想我刚才已经说过了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well,I..I think I just said.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.88,1:35:10.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯, 瑞普雷先生在帮我处理一些事务.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um, Mr. Ripley was handling some business for me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.95,1:35:14.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是瑞普雷先生想嫁给我...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Nor does Mr. Ripley want to marry me...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.37,1:35:18.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,并且每日每夜缠着你，问你什么时候结婚.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and ask me every single day if I'll marry him and when.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.88,1:35:21.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,你有瑞普雷先生的照片吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Do you keep a photograph of Signor Ripley ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.47,1:35:24.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,我没有随身携带男性朋友照片的习惯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm not in the habit of carrying around photographs of my male friends.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.63,1:35:28.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想我是让你困扰了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Now I think I've upset you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.65,1:35:32.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,对不起. 我的英语,可能,太差了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Sorry. My English,perhaps, is coarse.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.14,1:35:34.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,是有点差,是的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It is a little coarse,yes.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.65,1:35:39.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,我道歉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm sorry.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.65,1:35:45.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是你..没有人在圣雷默后见到过汤姆·瑞普雷.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But you..No one has seen Signor Ripley since San Remo.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.40,1:35:46.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我见过.   - 你见过, 是啊.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I have.   - You have, yes.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.70,1:35:49.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,舍伍德小姐也见过他.问问她. 还有, 嗯,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And so has Miss Sherwood.Ask her. And, um,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.46,1:35:54.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,让我想想他当时住在哪家旅馆...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}if I can remember the name of the hotel he was staying at...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.71,1:35:57.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯,高多尼旅馆.汤姆住在高多尼.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um, the Goldoni.Tom was staying at the Goldoni.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.84,1:36:01.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,高多尼.高多尼.很好,很好,但是...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Goldoni. The Goldoni.Good, good, but...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.31,1:36:03.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,是的,你是对的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yes, you are right.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.93,1:36:06.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是对的.纯属巧合.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You are right.A coincidence.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.37,1:36:07.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Siren Wailing, Distant]
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.27,1:36:12.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,我期待下一次见面.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Sighing ] I look forward to our next meeting.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.49,1:36:14.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯? 那时我会更注重我的英文的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hmm ? When I will be more careful with my English.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.09,1:36:18.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃.我有证人说当时看到两个男人...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Roverini] Ah. I have a witness who thinks they saw two men...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.37,1:36:20.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,进了迈尔斯先生的车.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}getting into Mr. Miles' car.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.37,1:36:24.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,她想来正面指证一下.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And she wants to identify you in a confronto.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.33,1:36:26.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,一组人.明天,怎么样?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Lineup. Tomorrow, then ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.34,1:36:30.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃,明天.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Uh, tomorrow.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.62,1:36:33.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chuckles ]
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.89,1:36:39.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 早上好,舍伍德小姐.   - 早上好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Buon giorno, Miss Sherwood. - Buon giorno.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.89,1:36:44.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,他在里面,不过我认为他现在真不想见任何人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He's in, but I really don't think he wants to meet anybody.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.10,1:36:53.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Knocking]
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.42,1:37:03.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dick ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.84,1:37:09.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.25,1:37:12.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你能听到我.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know you can hear me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.05,1:37:20.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sighing ]
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.32,1:37:24.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想说我会数到三,如果你不开门的话...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was gonna say that I would count to three, and if you didn't open the door...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.70,1:37:28.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,我就不会再……\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But I won't count anymore.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.03,1:37:31.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,指望你了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}On you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.08,1:37:37.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不会再指望你了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I won't count on you anymore.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.05,1:37:44.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,不管你做了什么没做什么,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Whatever it is you've done or haven't done,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.01,1:37:47.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,你已经伤透了我的心.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}you've broken my heart.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.77,1:37:52.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是我指认你的一项罪行.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That's one thing I know you're guilty of.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.78,1:38:02.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白是为了什么.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I don't know why.[ Sobbing ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.70,1:38:08.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白是为了什么.我就是不明白是为了什么.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know why.I just don't know why.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.56,1:38:11.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Footsteps Receding]
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.23,1:38:15.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Typewriter Keys Clattering]
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.31,1:38:17.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Thunder Rumbling]
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.97,1:38:20.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,我亲爱的汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Tom's Voice]My dear Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.26,1:38:23.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,我再也无法忍受了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I’m getting out of this.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.85,1:38:27.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,弗雷迪的死，希尔维那的死.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Freddie's death. Silvana.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.48,1:38:31.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,我曾经想过要去自首，但我不能.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I’ve thought about going to the police,but I can’t do it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.73,1:38:34.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我无法再面对这一切了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I can’t face it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.19,1:38:35.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,我再也无法面对这一切了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I can’t face anything anymore.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.86,1:38:36.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,我再也无法面对更多了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I can’t face anything anymore.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.03,1:38:39.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,我希望我能将我的生命交给你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I wish I could give you the life I took for granted.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.84,1:38:42.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Typewriter Bell Dings,Clattering Continues]
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.87,1:38:45.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,你总是能猜透我心里在想什么, 汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You've always understood what's at the heart of me, Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.43,1:38:48.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉永远都不能.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge never could.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.92,1:38:52.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想这就是为什么我给你写这封信的原因,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I suppose that's why I'm writing this to you,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.38,1:38:55.01,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是我唯一的兄弟.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}the brother I never had.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.09,1:38:58.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,也是我唯一真正的朋友.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The only true friend I ever had.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.19,1:39:05.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,从各方面来看,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}in all kinds of ways,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.19,1:39:09.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,你都更像是我父亲更想要的儿子.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}you're much more like the son my father wanted.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.90,1:39:13.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道你能改变人,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I realize you can change the people,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.20,1:39:15.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,改变风景,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}change the scenery,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.74,1:39:18.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,但却永远改变不了自己已经腐败的内心.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}but you can't change your own rotten self.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.75,1:39:23.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在我完全失去了方向.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Now I can't think what to do or where to go.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.26,1:39:29.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,我被一切不可挽回的错事所困扰.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I’m haunted by everything I’ve done and can’t undo.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.76,1:39:33.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,对不起.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I’m sorry.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.81,1:39:39.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,我把迪克·格林立夫的生活搞得一团糟，不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I've made a mess of being Dickie Greenleaf, haven't I ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.21,1:40:46.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,汤姆!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tom !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.73,1:40:52.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,我在那儿见你!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'll see you over there !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.84,1:40:55.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Bell Tolling]
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.41,1:41:02.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,真不好意思让你经历这些, 彼得.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm so sorry to put you through this, Peter.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.79,1:41:06.67,*Default,,0,0,0,,我只是无法在意大利语这么烂的情况下一个人去面对警方.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I just can't face going to the police by myself when my Italian's so rotten.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.69,1:41:08.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,别傻了.没事的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Don't be so daft.It's fine.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.49,1:41:10.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴你最终还是到了威尼斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm delighted you finally made it to Venice.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.25,1:41:13.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,我很开心,和谣言相反,你还好好的毫发无伤.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm delighted, contrary to rumor,that you're still in one piece.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.97,1:41:15.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么谣言?   - 哦,你知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What rumor ? - Oh, you know.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.05,1:41:19.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克谋杀了你，并冒用你的护照到处旅行.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That Dickie murdered you and is traveling under your passport.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.49,1:41:21.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道.这是很荒谬.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know. It's ridiculous.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.21,1:41:26.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Man Shouting in Italian]
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.42,1:41:29.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.42,1:41:32.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Phone Ringing]
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.49,1:41:38.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,欢迎来威尼斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Welcome to Venice.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.49,1:41:41.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,天啊,这地方很臭,不是吗?你闻到了吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}God, this place reeks, doesn't it ?Can you smell it ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.69,1:41:45.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,不管怎样, 我不能再推迟了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Anyway, I've got to the bottom of the delay, finally.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.19,1:41:48.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们在等从罗马来的警探.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We're waiting for someone from Rome.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.19,1:41:51.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,你说什么?他们从罗马派了人来?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What do you mean ?They've sent for someone from Rome ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.43,1:41:54.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 呃,是的.这挺好,不是吗?  - 不,我以为...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Well, yes. That's good, isn't it ? - No, I thought...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.26,1:41:57.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,在意大利不是这么运作的,我以为各地区都是独立的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}that didn't happen in Italy,that each region is separate.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.52,1:41:59.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,我肯定...我读过...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was sure that..I've read that..{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.10,1:42:03.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,你也读过报纸.你知道这件事有多重大.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You've read the papers.You know what a big deal it's been.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.02,1:42:06.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 美国游客被谋杀了.  - 但是,这件事能先搁一搁吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- American tourist murdered. - Actually, can we not do this now ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.15,1:42:10.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 这臭味真是..\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- The stench really is..- [Man Speaking Italian]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.59,1:42:16.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.27,1:42:27.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Continues in Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.51,1:42:32.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,他接管这个案子,是因为他们对前一任负责人很不满..\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He's taken over the case, 'cause they're annoyed that the previous chap...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.45,1:42:35.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,让弗雷德谋杀案唯一的嫌疑犯迪克,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}let Dickie disappear when he was, um,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.34,1:42:37.15,*Default,,0,0,0,,就这么失踪了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}the only suspect in Freddie’s murder.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.56,1:42:39.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.19,1:42:43.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,在罗马，大约三周以前.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}In Rome,about three weeks ago.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.53,1:42:45.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,这句我能听懂.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I knew that one.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.53,1:42:50.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯..\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Um..[ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.49,1:42:52.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.71,1:42:58.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,你是同性恋吗?有趣的不知所云.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Are you a homosexual ?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14}{\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Interesting non sequitur.{\c}{\c}{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.44,1:42:59.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.72,1:43:02.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 不是.  - 噢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- No.    - Oh.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.01,1:43:07.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,顺便说一下, 嗯,官方是没有意大利同性恋这种讲法的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}By the way, um, officially there are no Italian homosexuals.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.02,1:43:10.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,这让米开朗基罗和莱昂纳多很是困扰.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Makes Michelangelo and Leonardo very inconvenient.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.52,1:43:12.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Eh ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.35,1:43:15.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,告诉他...我有个未婚妻.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tell him...I have a fiancée.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.85,1:43:18.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克也有个未婚妻.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And Dickie has a fiancée.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.07,1:43:21.70,*Default,,0,0,0,,至于那个弗雷迪·迈尔斯,他没准有一打的未婚妻.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And that Freddie Miles probably had a string of them.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.41,1:43:23.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.38,1:43:37.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,我的老天呀.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Mamma mia.[ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.27,1:43:40.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,- [Inspector Laughing]\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Chuckling ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.85,1:43:43.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 他说了什么?   - 他说"这么多未婚妻."\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What did he say ?  - He says "so many fiancées."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.66,1:43:46.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.23,1:43:51.63,*Default,,0,0,0,,他问...是不是你杀了弗雷迪·迈尔斯...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He’s asking... if you killed Freddie Miles...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.68,1:43:53.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,然后又杀了迪克·格林立夫.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and then killed Dickie Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.28,1:43:57.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,不! 没有,我没有杀弗雷迪·迈尔斯,更没有杀迪克·格林立夫.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No ! No, I did not kill Freddie Miles and then kill Dickie Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.52,1:44:00.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,他是在指控我吗?问问他他是否在指控我.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Is he accusing me ?Ask him if he's accusingme.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.54,1:44:03.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,这里的办事程序就是这样,这总比严刑逼供好多了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The way it works here,it's better to be less volatile.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.42,1:44:05.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,-但这也太荒谬了!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- But it’s absurd!- [ Italian ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.29,1:44:07.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.54,1:44:17.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.10,1:44:25.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们在迪克罗马的寓所里发现了这个.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}They found this in Dickie's place in Rome.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.69,1:44:28.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你打开过?   -当然.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- You opened this ?  - Of course.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.55,1:44:47.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,这是一封遗书.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's a suicide note.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.18,1:44:55.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,你早就看过这份遗书,还问我这些问题?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You asked me all these questions and you already read this suicide note ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.42,1:45:15.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不相信那封遗书.你呢?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't believe that letter.Do you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.50,1:45:19.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克的信.你相信吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie's letter.Do you believe it ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.17,1:45:22.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道什么该相信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know what to believe.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.27,1:45:26.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,那你能想象吗，如果是他杀了弗雷迪，那会是怎样一个情形？\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Can you imagine, though, if he did kill Freddie, what that must be like ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.51,1:45:30.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,每天早上照常醒来.我是说,你怎么能做到?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Just to wake up every morning.I mean, how can you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.43,1:45:34.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,醒来像个常人一样的生活?喝你的咖啡.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Just wake up and be a person ?Drink your coffee.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.18,1:45:38.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃,不管你做了什么，不管有过可怕，不管有多痛苦,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, whatever you do,however terrible, however hurtful,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.44,1:45:41.78,*Default,,0,0,0,,它都是有意义的,不是吗,在你的头脑里.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}it all makes sense,doesn't it, in your head.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.82,1:45:45.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,你从未遇到过自认为是坏人的人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You never meet anybody who thinks they're a bad person.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.68,1:45:48.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,没有, 我知道,但是你仍然饱受煎熬.你一定会这样.你杀了人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, I know, but you're still tormented.You must be. You've killed someone.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.79,1:45:51.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,你不会将过去放进地下室的房间里吗？\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Don't you just take the past and put it in a room in the basement,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.00,1:45:53.96,*Default,,0,0,0,,锁上门，再也不走进去?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and lock the door and never go in there ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.05,1:45:57.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,-那是我会做的.   -上帝啊,是这样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- That's what I do. - God, yes.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.47,1:46:02.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过,当然,按我的情况,可能需要一整幢楼来装我的记忆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But, of course, in my case,it's probably a whole building.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.18,1:46:05.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,-然后你遇到一个对你而言特别的人,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}-  [ Piano: Stops ]- And then you meet someone special,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.31,1:46:09.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,你想做的只是扔给他们这把钥匙.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and all you want to do is toss them the key.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.69,1:46:13.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,说 "开了.进来吧."\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Say "Open up. Step inside."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.99,1:46:18.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是你不能...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But you can't...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.28,1:46:21.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,-因为里面很黑...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Resumes]- because it's dark...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.12,1:46:24.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,还有恶魔.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and there are demons.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.04,1:46:27.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,一旦有人看见里面有多肮脏...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And if anybody saw how ugly it is...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.22,1:46:34.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在是音乐在影响你的情绪\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Now that's the music talking.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.51,1:46:39.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果你是在弹“站起来，布朗妈妈”想忧郁也难了\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's harder to be bleak if you're playing "Knees Up, Mother Brown."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.56,1:46:48.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,我一直都想……\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I keep wanting to do that.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.53,1:46:52.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,冲开门...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Fling...the door open.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.62,1:46:54.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Resumes]
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.87,1:46:59.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,让阳光洒进来，把一切都清洗干净.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Just let the light in,clean everything out.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.92,1:47:04.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果我有一块巨大的橡皮,能擦除一切\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}If I could take a giant eraser and rub out everything,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.00,1:47:07.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,从我自己开始...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}starting with myself...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.51,1:47:13.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,问题在于,彼得,如果...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The thing is, Peter, if...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.27,1:47:19.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗯?   - 如果...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Hmm ?  - If...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.73,1:47:23.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}If...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.74,1:47:33.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果没有钥匙,对吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No key, huh ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.64,1:47:35.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Boy Singing in Latin]
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.38,1:47:50.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.51,1:48:19.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,-玛吉.   -彼得.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Marge.  - Peter.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.97,1:48:23.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,-很高兴见到你.  -你好，玛吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- So good to see you.  - Hello, Marge.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.97,1:48:26.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.27,1:48:30.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我发现你找到了彼得.  -我想是我们彼此找到了对方.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I see you found Peter. - I think we sort of found each other.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.40,1:48:34.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,-迪克的父亲在哪儿?  -他今天早上才能到.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Where's Dickie's father ? - He's not coming till the morning.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.19,1:48:37.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,他的胃.我觉得这儿的食物不适合他.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Evidently his stomach. I don't think the food here is agreeing with him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:37.82,1:48:39.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,我很期待见到他.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, I was looking forward to seeing him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.83,1:48:42.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克没有自杀.我确信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie hasn't killed himself.I'm sure of that.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.54,1:48:45.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在有一位私人侦探正着手调查此案.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There's a private detective on the case now.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.25,1:48:47.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,麦卡伦先生，迪克的父亲雇来的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}A Mr. MacCarron Dickie's father's employed.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.83,1:48:51.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 这太好了.  - 他是个美国人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- That's a terrific idea. - He's American.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.25,1:48:54.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,他已经查出迪克在失踪前一天...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He's already discovered that Dickie cashed checks for $1 ,000...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.59,1:48:56.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,刚取了1000美元.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}the day before he disappeared.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.93,1:48:58.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,小姐.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Man ]Signora.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.93,1:49:02.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,你在跳进台伯河前会这样做吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Is that what you do before you jump into the Tiber ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.43,1:49:05.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不这么认为.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don’t think so.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.86,1:49:11.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,-这是你的?   -不，这是汤姆的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Is this you ? - No, it's Tom's.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.15,1:49:13.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,很不错，不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Splendid, eh ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.16,1:49:16.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,天啊.谁付的房租?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Golly.Who's paying for this ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.53,1:49:18.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,彼得替我找的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Peter found it for me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.58,1:49:23.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,我能付的起是因为这里又潮湿...又破旧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I can afford it because it's damp and... falling down.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.54,1:49:26.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,-汤姆改造过这房子.   -太棒了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Tom's transformed it. - This is spectacular.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.80,1:49:29.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么汤姆希望你能住下来.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That's why Tom wanted you to stay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.13,1:49:31.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,这总比挤在我的小屋里好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's better than trying to squeeze into my room.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.80,1:49:33.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你讨厌旅馆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I know how you hate hotels.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.97,1:49:35.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,旅馆就可以了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}A hotel would have been fine.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.44,1:49:43.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们得告诉格林立夫先生.他的佣金已经用到哪儿了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We'll have to tell Mr. Greenleaf how far his dollar stretched.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.36,1:49:50.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,-什么这么可笑?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Chuckles ]- What's funny ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.45,1:49:53.99,*Default,,0,0,0,,我只是想起汤姆第一次来蒙吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was just thinking about when Tom first came to Mongibello.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.04,1:49:59.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,-再看看你现在.   -看我什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- And look at you now. - Look at me what ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.75,1:50:02.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,贵族出生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}To the manor born.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.31,1:50:06.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Bell Tolling]
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.90,1:50:19.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Tom]Mr. Greenleaf?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.60,1:50:22.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Continues]
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.99,1:50:24.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Mr. Greenleaf?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.99,1:50:29.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,汤姆.你好吗?你看起来真不错.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tom. How are you ?You look well.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.49,1:50:32.12,*Default,,0,0,0,,-谢谢你,先生，我还不错.  -和在纽约时判若两人啊.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Thank you, sir. I am well. - Far cry from New York.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.12,1:50:34.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,-是啊.   -玛吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Yes, it is.  - Marge.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.25,1:50:37.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,早上好.不寻常的天气.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Good morning.Unusual weather.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.38,1:50:40.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,-是呀.  -你呢,先生.好点了吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Very. - And you, sir. Any better ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.30,1:50:43.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,很好.用热水捂着.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Pretty good.Sticking with hot water.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.51,1:50:45.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,-麦卡隆先生呢?  -在圣雷默.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Where's Mr. MacCarron ?- San Remo.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.89,1:50:48.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,警察都是业余的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The police are amateurs.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.84,1:50:53.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃,我的孩子,不错的转变,不是吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, my boy, it's come to a pretty pass, hasn't it ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.31,1:50:56.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,侦探在圣雷默找什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What is the detective hoping to find in San Remo ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.69,1:51:01.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,他在进行地毯式的搜索.我正在了解我的儿子,汤姆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He's being thorough.I'm learning about my son, Tom.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.49,1:51:04.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,现在他失踪了,我了解到很多关于他的事,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Now he's missing,I'm learning a great deal about him,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.00,1:51:08.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你能帮我填上一些空白.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and I hope that you can fill in some more blanks for me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.17,1:51:11.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉已经将蒙吉那部分填得差不多了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge has been good enough to do that about Mongibello.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.29,1:51:15.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,我会尽最大努力的,先生.很明显,我会为迪克做一切事情.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'll try my best, sir. Obviously,I'll do anything to help Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.17,1:51:18.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,-很好.这个理论,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}-[Continues]- Good. This theory,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.53,1:51:19.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,他留给你的那封信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}the letter he left for you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.93,1:51:23.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,警察认为这清楚地指出了...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The police think that's a clear indication...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.27,1:51:27.02,*Default,,0,0,0,,他打算对自己,呃,做些事情.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}he was planning on doing something,uh, to himself.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.06,1:51:29.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不相信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I just don't believe that.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.94,1:51:32.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,亲爱的,你只是不愿去相信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You don't want to, dear.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.24,1:51:37.84,*Default,,0,0,0,,我想和汤姆单独谈谈.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'd like to talk to Tom alone.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.98,1:51:40.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,也许就这个下午.你觉得呢?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Perhaps this afternoon.Would you mind?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.04,1:51:47.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉,一个男人对他的爱人所说的...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, what a man may say to his sweetheart...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.13,1:51:50.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,和对他的朋友所说的（是不一样的）...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and what he'll admit to another fellow...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.59,1:51:55.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,比如说?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Such as ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.42,1:51:58.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Continues]
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.02,1:52:02.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,真是在浪费生命和机遇.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Clears Throat ]What a waste of lives and opportunities.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.76,1:52:05.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,我宁可付100美元给那个萨克斯手让他闭嘴!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'd pay that fellow a hundred dollars right now to shut up !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.23,1:52:16.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,不,玛吉连一半都不知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, Marge doesn't know the half of it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.12,1:52:20.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,还有他的护照照片.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And his passport photo.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.46,1:52:23.65,*Default,,0,0,0,,你听说了吗？把他自己的脸划成那个样子?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Did you hear ? To scratch out his own face like that ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.66,1:52:25.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,你能想象吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Can you imagine ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.59,1:52:28.93,*Default,,0,0,0,,他一定要这样钻牛角尖吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Frame of mind you'd have to be in ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.01,1:52:32.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,"我想过要去自首,但是我不能.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}"I've thought about going to the police,but I can't face it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.39,1:52:35.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,我再也忍受不了了."\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I can't face anything anymore."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.98,1:52:39.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得愧疚.我觉得是我把他推开了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I feel guilty. I feel like I pushed him away.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.40,1:52:41.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得每当我开口劝阻,他听到的都是你的声音.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I feel like I spoke and he heard you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.53,1:52:44.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,嗯,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well,[ Clears Throat ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.40,1:52:47.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,与其说是我们把他推开了,还不如说是他把我们都推开了吧?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}if we all pushed him away,what about him pushing us away ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.41,1:52:49.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,你曾经是我儿子最好的朋友.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You've been a great friend to my son.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.74,1:52:52.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,每件事都是别人的错.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Everything is someone else's fault.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.96,1:52:55.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们都想让他放任自流,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We all want to sow wild oats,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.50,1:52:58.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是总有人得...得...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}but somebody's got to...got to...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.88,1:53:01.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,怎么说来着?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What is the word ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.01,1:53:04.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道,当有人和他对峙的时候,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You know, the moment someone confronts him,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.35,1:53:08.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,他总是痛殴对方.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}he lashes out.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.93,1:53:11.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,他总是这样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He always has.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.56,1:53:16.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道, 人们总是说你不能选择你的父母,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You know, people always say that you can't choose your parents,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.20,1:53:23.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,但是你也不能选择你的孩子.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}but you can't choose your children.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.03,1:53:27.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Knocking]- [Freddie's Voice] Dickie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.72,1:53:31.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,你就像个吸血水蛭.你很令人厌烦.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Dickie's Voice] You can be a leech. You can be quite boring.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.58,1:53:33.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,-住手!    -令人厌烦.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Tom's Voice] Stop it ! - [Dickie's Voice] It's boring.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.31,1:53:36.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,- [Knocking]\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Voices Overlapping, indistinct]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:37.38,1:53:40.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,住手,住手,住手!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Tom Screaming]Stop, stop, stop !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.22,1:53:43.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,-住手,住手,住手!   - 汤米,汤米.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Stop, stop, stop ! - [Freddie's Voice] Tommy, Tommy.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.22,1:53:45.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,像个小姑娘.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Dickie's Voice]Like a little girl.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.23,1:53:48.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,像个小姑娘.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Like a little girl.- [Knocking]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.41,1:53:49.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Knocking]
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.94,1:53:53.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,来了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Knocking]- Coming.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.99,1:53:57.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 不好意思.我睡着了.   - 总算开了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Sorry. I was asleep. - Finally.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.21,1:53:58.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我一定是睡着了.   -迪克的爸爸走了吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I must have fallen asleep. - Did Dickie's dad go ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.62,1:54:00.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,你看起来气色很差,汤姆.是发噩梦了吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You look ghastly, Tom.Did you have a nightmare ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.62,1:54:03.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,-他时差还没调过来.  -噢,可怜的老人.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- He's having an early night. - Oh, poor man.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.92,1:54:06.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道,我们会无休无止地敲下去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You know, we were banging on that door forever.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:09.96,1:54:11.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢-不.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Marge]Uh-oh.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.97,1:54:15.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我想我弄断了一根吊带.   -别介意.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I think I've broken a strap. - Not guilty.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.64,1:54:18.60,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我来弄点喝的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I'll fix some drinks.- [ Marge Giggling ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.60,1:54:21.31,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢!这就是在威尼斯步行.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ah !You walk in Venice.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.85,1:54:24.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Are you okay ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:26.27,1:54:28.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我很好.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm fine.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.19,1:54:33.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你想让我留下吗?   -不用了,没关系.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Did you want me to stick around ? - No, it's okay.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:34.41,1:54:36.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,我会回来的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I could come back.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.93,1:54:54.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,你的钥匙.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Your key.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:57.77,1:55:00.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,-汤姆?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Knocking At Door]- [Marge] Tom ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.52,1:55:04.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉,我在洗澡.不需要太久的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, I'm in the bath.I won't be long.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:04.11,1:55:06.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,汤姆,我必须同你谈谈.非常紧急.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tom, I have to speak to you.It’s urgent.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.58,1:55:11.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,来了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Coming.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.01,1:55:26.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我找到了迪克的戒指.  -什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I found Dickie's rings. - What ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.38,1:55:28.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,你拿了迪克的戒指.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You have Dickie's rings.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.89,1:55:28.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.18,1:55:35.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,这点我可以解释.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I can explain.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.18,1:55:38.85,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克向我保证过他决不会摘掉这个戒指.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie promised me he would never take off this ring.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.94,1:55:40.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,先让我穿上点衣服再来讨论此事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Let me put some clothes on and we'll talk about this.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:41.07,1:55:43.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 我必须告诉格林立夫先生.  - 玛吉,你太过敏了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- I have to tell Mr. Greenleaf. - Marge, you're being hysterical.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.59,1:55:48.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,他向我保证过, "我发誓,我绝不会摘掉这个戒指直到我们结..."\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He promised me, "I swear, I will never take off this ring until we get..."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.10,1:55:49.03,*Default,,0,0,0,,-闭嘴!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Shut up !- [ Gasping ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.24,1:55:55.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,我湿透了,玛吉.我的毛巾也掉了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm wet, Marge.I've lost my towel.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.39,1:55:57.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,我真的得穿上些衣服.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I’d really like to put some clothes on.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.97,1:55:59.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,去给我们俩倒杯酒好吗.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Go and pour us both a drink.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.30,1:56:05.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,倒杯酒.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Pour us a drink.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.58,1:56:40.92,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:41.00,1:56:43.25,*Default,,0,0,0,,你要去哪儿?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Where are you going ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:43.34,1:56:46.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,我没有乱翻.我只是...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I wasn't snooping.I just...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.88,1:56:50.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,我只是想找针线缝一下我的文胸.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was looking for a needle and thread to mend my bra.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:51.80,1:56:55.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,你在用的这瓶香水.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That scent you're wearing.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.47,1:56:58.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,是我买的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I bought that for you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.77,1:57:01.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,关于迪克的一些事...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The thing about Dickie...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.44,1:57:03.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,很多事.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So many things.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.27,1:57:09.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,那天他从罗马回来晚了,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}That day when he was late coming back from Rome,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:09.65,1:57:10.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,我曾经尝试着告诉你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I tried to tell you this.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.95,1:57:15.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,他是和其它女孩好上了.我并不是指梅瑞迪斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He was with another girl.I'm not talking about Meredith, either.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.49,1:57:17.75,*Default,,0,0,0,,另一个在酒吧里认识的女孩.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Another girl that we met in a bar.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:17.79,1:57:20.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,他连五分钟的忠诚都保证不了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He couldn't be faithful for five minutes.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.96,1:57:23.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以当他作其它一些保证的时候,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So when he makes a promise,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.74,1:57:25.79,*Default,,0,0,0,,并不像你我许诺一样...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}it doesn't mean what it means when you make a promise...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14}{\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}1663{\c}{\c}{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.82,1:57:27.76,*Default,,0,0,0,,会信守到底.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}or I make a promise.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.80,1:57:32.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,他有那么多的现实,迪克,而他又全部相信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He has so many realities, Dickie,and he believes them all.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:32.88,1:57:35.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,他撒谎.他撒谎.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He lies. He lies.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.54,1:57:39.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,那还只是一半的情况,有时他甚至意识不到他在背叛誓言.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And that's his...Half the time he doesn't even realize he's doing it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:39.74,1:57:42.94,*Default,,0,0,0,,而今天,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And today,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.98,1:57:46.77,*Default,,0,0,0,,我开始怀疑是否是他谋杀了弗雷迪.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I really started wondering whether he may have killed Freddie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.86,1:57:51.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果有人站出来和他对抗,他会变得如此疯狂.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He would get so crazy if anybody would contradict him.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:51.56,1:57:54.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,是这样,你知道这一点.你知道这一点.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, you know that.You know that.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.32,1:57:55.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道这一点.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You know that.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:55.99,1:57:58.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是讽刺的地方,玛吉.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And that's the irony, Marge.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.33,1:58:00.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I loved you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:00.33,1:58:03.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,你也许已经知道,玛吉.我爱你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You may as well know, Marge.I loved you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.40,1:58:05.98,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道这时候说这个会很怪异,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know, maybe it's grotesque of me to say this now,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.03,1:58:09.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以...就请在一张纸或别的什么东西上...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}so just... write it on apiece of paper or something...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.39,1:58:11.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,写上"汤姆爱我,汤姆爱我"\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}and put it in your purse for a rainy day.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.39,1:58:14.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,放到你的钱包里,将来也许可以作为慰籍.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}"Tom loves me. Tom loves me."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:14.89,1:58:18.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你为什么会有迪克的戒指    -我告诉过你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Why do you have Dickie's rings ?  - I told you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:18.35,1:58:21.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,-是他给我的.  -为什么?什么时候?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- He gave them to me.  - Why ? When ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:21.44,1:58:24.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你刚才完全没有在听我对你说的话.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I feel as if you haven't been listening to anything I've been saying to you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.50,1:58:27.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不相信你.我不相信你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't believe you.I don't believe you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.62,1:58:30.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,-这都是真的.    -你说的话...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- It's all true.  - I don't believe...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.36,1:58:33.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,我一个字也不相信.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}a single word you've said.[ Gasping, Shuddering ]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:33.82,1:58:37.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,你在发抖,玛吉.看看你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You're shivering, Marge.Look at you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:37.62,1:58:40.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉,我能抱着你吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, can I hold you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.50,1:58:42.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,你能让我抱着你吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Will you let me hold you ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:42.54,1:58:45.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,-玛吉?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [ Screaming ]- Marge ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:45.61,1:58:48.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,-彼得!感谢上天你来了.   -怎么了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Peter ! Thank God you're here. - What’s going on ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:48.54,1:58:52.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,带我走.带我走.求求你了!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Get me out of here.Get me out of here. Please!{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:52.26,1:58:56.09,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 汤姆,你还好吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Peter] Tom, are you okay ?- [Marge Sobbing]{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:58:56.14,1:59:00.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,你试试.你试着劝劝她.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You try.You try talking to her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:01.35,1:59:03.23,*Default,,0,0,0,,-汤姆?   -我放弃.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Peter] Tom ? - I give up.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:03.42,1:59:06.10,*Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我到底发生了什么.汤姆!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Tell me what's going on.Tom !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:06.19,1:59:08.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,-我从未对她做过什么,我对她做过什么吗?  -听着...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- [Tom] What did I ever do to her? - Listen...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.63,1:59:10.86,*Default,,0,0,0,,她能说出一件我曾经伤害过她的事吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Have her tell you one thing that I've ever done to her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:10.94,1:59:13.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,听着，你不能同她怄气.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You can't be angry with her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:13.70,1:59:17.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,她很迷惑,她需要一个迁怒的对象.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}She's confused, and she needs someone to blame.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.49,1:59:18.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以她迁怒于你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}So she blames you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:18.70,1:59:21.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,我会回去和她好好谈谈.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'll go back home and talk to her.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.53,1:59:23.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,至于你,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}As for you,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:23.91,1:59:27.54,*Default,,0,0,0,,要么换个安全剃刀,要么就留胡子吧.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}either get a safety razor or grow a beard.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:34.97,1:59:36.88,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Knocking]
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.55,1:59:43.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,-格林立夫先生在吗?-瑞普雷先生?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Is Mr. Greenleaf here ?  - Mr. Ripley ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:43.61,1:59:46.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,-是我. -我是阿尔文·麦克隆.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Yes. - I'm Alvin MacCarron.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:48.19,1:59:51.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道,我不知道.我就知道是这样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Marge] I don't know,I don't know. I just know it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.67,1:59:55.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉,这只是女性的直觉，然而事实……\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Mr. Greenleaf] Marge, there's female intuition and then there are facts.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:57.35,1:59:58.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,-汤姆.   -先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Tom.   - Sir.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,1:59:58.67,2:00:02.16,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉,你该等一等的.我没有...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, you should have waited.I didn't...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:02.24,2:00:04.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,彼得没有告诉你我会顺道去接你吗?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Didn't Peter say I'd come by and pick you up ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:05.74,2:00:08.37,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉在对我们说戒指的事情.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge has been telling us about the rings.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:08.38,2:00:11.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,是啊,我也觉得很荒谬,我昨天并没有提起.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yes, I feel ridiculous I didn't mention them yesterday.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:11.29,2:00:13.71,*Default,,0,0,0,,我完全忘了.太荒谬了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I clean forgot.Ridiculous.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:15.60,2:00:20.59,*Default,,0,0,0,,也许只有一个理由能解释为什么你没有告诉我们.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Perhaps you didn't mention them because there's only one conclusion to be drawn.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:21.68,2:00:25.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,我带玛吉去散散步.汤姆,麦克隆先生需要和你谈谈.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I'm going to take Marge for a walk.Tom, Mr. MacCarron needs to talk to you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:25.92,2:00:28.20,*Default,,0,0,0,,没必要吧.我们可以一起去酒吧.没这个必要.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There's no need. We could go to the bar. There's no need.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.21,2:00:29.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,不,不.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}No, no.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:30.36,2:00:32.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,我认为你应该呆在这里.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I think you should stay here.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:34.36,2:00:37.53,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Door Opening, Closing]
Dialogue: 0,2:00:53.71,2:00:56.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,我能从这儿看到我的房间.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I could probably see my room from here.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.29,2:00:59.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,我能看到我的房子.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I can see my house.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:00.22,2:01:04.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,当你从远方眺望你的家时,感觉就像是在做梦,是不是?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}When you see where you live from a distance, it's like a dream, isn't it ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:04.43,2:01:06.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,我没时间瞎扯\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't care for B.S.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:06.77,2:01:10.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不想听.也不想说.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't care to hear it.I don't care to speak it.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:12.60,2:01:15.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,-好吧.   -你知道在普林斯顿的时候...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Okay.  - Did you know that at Princeton...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:15.54,2:01:17.28,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克·格林立夫差点打死了一个男孩?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie Greenleaf half-killed a boy ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:17.36,2:01:19.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,在一个聚会上为了些女孩争风吃醋.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}At a party over some girl.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:19.45,2:01:23.32,*Default,,0,0,0,,踹了那男孩的头好几脚,把他送进了医院.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Kicked the kid several times in the head, put him in the hospital.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:23.41,2:01:27.35,*Default,,0,0,0,,男孩的下巴得用铁丝固定,丧失了部分听力.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Boy had a wire fixed in his jaw,lost some hearing.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:27.39,2:01:31.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,你以为为什么迪克的父亲最初要把他送到欧洲来?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Why do you think Dickie's father sent him to Europe in the first place ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:33.29,2:01:37.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,罗马警局没想到来问格林立夫先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The Rome police didn't think to ask Mr. Greenleaf.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:37.59,2:01:41.55,*Default,,0,0,0,,也没想过要去查查汤姆斯·瑞普雷是否真的...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Nor did they think to check on whether a Thomas Ripley...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:41.59,2:01:43.80,*Default,,0,0,0,,曾经在普林斯顿上学.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}had ever been a student at Princeton University.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:43.89,2:01:48.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢,我发现汤姆·瑞普雷...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, I turned up a Tom Ripley...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:48.60,2:01:53.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,原来只是音乐系的一个钢琴调音师.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}who had been a piano tuner in the music department.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:54.77,2:01:56.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,你看,在美国,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You see, in America,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:01:56.24,2:02:01.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们总是被教育要防患于未然.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}we are taught to check a fact before it becomes a fact.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:01.23,2:02:02.95,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们被训练去四处探听.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We're taught to nose around.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:02.99,2:02:05.87,*Default,,0,0,0,,如果一个女孩溺水死了,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}When a girl drowns herself,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:05.95,2:02:08.33,*Default,,0,0,0,,查查看她是否怀孕了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}find out if that girl is pregnant.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:08.41,2:02:12.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,查查看迪克是不是有什么不可告人的秘密.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Find out if Dickie had an embarrassment there.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:12.75,2:02:16.13,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生非常欣赏你的忠诚.他真的很欣赏.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Mr. Greenleaf appreciates your loyalty.He really does.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:16.17,2:02:19.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉...她能有上百种推论.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge...She has a hundred theories.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:19.34,2:02:22.26,*Default,,0,0,0,,有些事情是她不知道的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}There are a few things that she doesn't know.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:22.34,2:02:24.30,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望她永远也不要知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}We hope she never knows.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:24.39,2:02:27.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望她永远也不要知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I hope she never knows.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:27.48,2:02:29.18,*Default,,0,0,0,,三个不同的人...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Three different people...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:29.27,2:02:32.81,*Default,,0,0,0,,看见迪克进了弗雷迪的车.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}saw Dickie get into Freddie's car.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:32.89,2:02:36.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,其中一个,并不会指认...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}One man,who will not testify...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:36.27,2:02:39.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,因为他当时是在和别人的妻子通奸,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}because he was jumping somebody else's wife at the time,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:39.58,2:02:43.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,他看到迪克从一辆红色跑车上取下牌照.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}saw Dickie removing license plates from a red sports car.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.60,2:02:48.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,警方之所以知道是因为这人本身就是个警察.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The police know about this man because he happens to be a policeman.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:50.17,2:02:52.83,*Default,,0,0,0,,我在迪克的地下室里发现了这些.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I found these in the basement of Dickie's apartment.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:52.91,2:02:55.00,*Default,,0,0,0,,它们是弗雷迪的车上的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}They belong to Freddie's car.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:55.08,2:02:59.38,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生叫我...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Mr. Greenleaf has asked me...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:02:59.46,2:03:03.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,把这些扔到运河里去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}to lose these in the canal this evening.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:04.84,2:03:07.47,*Default,,0,0,0,,[Bell Tolling]
Dialogue: 0,2:03:08.35,2:03:10.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,格林立夫先生说他从迪克给你的信中...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Mr. Greenleaf feels that there was a silent promise...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:10.57,2:03:13.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,觉察到了迪克对你的一些秘密承诺.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}in Dickie's letter to you which he intends to honor.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:13.73,2:03:16.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,他已经打算将迪克收入的一大部分...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He also intends to transfer a good portion...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:16.35,2:03:21.07,*Default,,0,0,0,,转入你的账户.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}of Dickie's income from his trust into your name.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:21.15,2:03:23.24,*Default,,0,0,0,,他不想让...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He does not intend...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:23.32,2:03:27.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,意大利人知道任何关于迪克的过去.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}to give the Italians any information about Dickie's past.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:28.74,2:03:33.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,他宁可希望...你也是这样想的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He's rather hoping that...you will feel the same.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:51.30,2:03:53.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 非常感谢,汤姆.   - 先生.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Thank you so much, Tom. - Sir.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:53.60,2:03:54.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,再见.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Good-bye.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:03:58.75,2:04:03.64,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉, 我希望我那天晚上从未对你说过那些话.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge, I feel I never should have said those things to you the other evening.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:03.65,2:04:08.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,我太慌乱了,还有戒指...你看起来又那么...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was pretty flustered,and the rings...And you looked so...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:08.61,2:04:09.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:09.95,2:04:14.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,但我希望你钱包里那张纸条能和你一回纽约...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But I hope that note goes in your purse to New York...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:14.52,2:04:16.58,*Default,,0,0,0,,总有一天会用上的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}for a rainy day.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:17.82,2:04:22.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你现在打算干吗,汤姆?   -我不知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What are you gonna do now, Tom ? - I don't know.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:22.52,2:04:25.05,*Default,,0,0,0,,彼得下个月在雅典有场音乐会,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Peter has a concert in Athens next month,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:25.13,2:04:27.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,所以他问我是否愿意一起去帮帮他的忙.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}so he asked me to come along and help out.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:29.30,2:04:31.22,*Default,,0,0,0,,他向你告别.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}He says good-bye.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:31.30,2:04:34.56,*Default,,0,0,0,,对了,他正在预演所以不能来...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}By the way, he was in rehearsal so he couldn't...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:34.57,2:04:37.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我觉得瑞普雷永远都不会陷入困境?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Why do I think there's never been a Ripley rainy day ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:37.60,2:04:40.19,*Default,,0,0,0,,什么?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}What ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:40.27,2:04:44.48,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道是你干的.我知道是你干的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know it was you.I know it was you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:44.57,2:04:46.90,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道是你干的!我知道是你干的!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I know it was you !I know it was you !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:44.67,2:04:47.51,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,2:04:46.99,2:04:50.62,*Default,,0,0,0,,-玛吉,玛吉.别这样!   -我知道是你杀了迪克!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Marge, Marge. Please ! - I know you killed Dickie !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:50.70,2:04:53.39,*Default,,0,0,0,,-玛吉!   -我知道!不!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Marge ! - I know ! No !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:53.40,2:04:56.50,*Default,,0,0,0,,我知道是你干的!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Sobbing ]I know it was you !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:56.59,2:04:58.69,*Default,,0,0,0,,玛吉.玛吉,别这样.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Marge.Marge, please.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:04:58.70,2:05:02.04,*Default,,0,0,0,,不是汤姆.真的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}It's not Tom.Really.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:10.43,2:05:13.89,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们是凤尾船船夫\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Tom And Peter]We are called gondoleri{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:13.90,2:05:17.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,不过那只是幻想,那是无上的光荣\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}But that's a vagary It's quite honorary{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:17.74,2:05:22.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,我们的往返旅途\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}The trade that we ply{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:22.82,2:05:26.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,问我这一刻我想改变什么.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Ask me what I want to change about this moment.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:26.36,2:05:28.72,*Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道. 你想改变这一刻?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I don't know. What do you want to change about this moment ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:28.73,2:05:29.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,什么也不变.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Nothing.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:34.74,2:05:36.74,*Default,,0,0,0,,我冷死了.一起下去?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[ Peter ]I'm freezing. Coming down ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:36.75,2:05:39.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,过一会. 我想看看日落.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Later. I want to catch the sunset.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:39.54,2:05:44.29,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你疯了.     -我是疯了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- You're mad. [ Chuckling ]  - I am.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:53.22,2:05:55.14,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}[Meredith]Dickie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:05:58.35,2:06:00.27,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:03.69,2:06:05.61,*Default,,0,0,0,,迪克!\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Dickie !{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:12.57,2:06:15.49,*Default,,0,0,0,,[ Italian ]
Dialogue: 0,2:06:17.70,2:06:19.52,*Default,,0,0,0,,哦,我的天.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, my God.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:21.58,2:06:23.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,你好,梅瑞迪斯.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hello, Meredith.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:26.57,2:06:28.40,*Default,,0,0,0,,我刚一直在看你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I was looking at you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:28.49,2:06:32.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,你的衣服.我差点就认不出来了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Your clothes.I wouldn't have known you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:32.59,2:06:35.34,*Default,,0,0,0,,呃,你发现了我,所以你拿到了你的奖励.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Well, you spotted me,so you get the reward.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:36.61,2:06:38.68,*Default,,0,0,0,,-什么?   -开玩笑.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- What ? -Just kidding.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:38.77,2:06:42.73,*Default,,0,0,0,,-你一个人?   -噢.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Are you alone ?  - Oh.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:42.77,2:06:46.41,*Default,,0,0,0,,难说.孤单的不能再孤单了.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Hardly.Couldn't be less alone.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:43.39,2:06:46.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,2:06:46.60,2:06:49.57,*Default,,0,0,0,,-琼阿姨.  -还有叔叔\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Aunt Joan.  - And "co."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:52.69,2:06:54.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,太多叔叔了\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}A lot of "co."{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:55.38,2:06:57.91,*Default,,0,0,0,,噢,天.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Oh, God.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:57.99,2:07:02.08,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道,再次看到你, 我...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You know, seeing you again, I...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:02.76,2:07:06.46,*Default,,0,0,0,,在想你...\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I've thought about you...{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:06.49,2:07:08.66,*Default,,0,0,0,,一直.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}so much.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:08.70,2:07:11.06,*Default,,0,0,0,,我也在想你.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}And I've thought about you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:13.01,2:07:16.97,*Default,,0,0,0,,是呀,不过,当我想到你的时候,我可是很恨你的.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Yeah, well, when I've thought about you,I was mostly hating you.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:23.26,2:07:25.42,*Default,,0,0,0,,你躲哪儿去了?\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Where have you been hiding ?{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:25.60,2:07:28.11,*Default,,0,0,0,,我没躲.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I haven't been hiding.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:28.19,2:07:31.43,*Default,,0,0,0,,我被警察看守.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}I've been in police custody.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:32.36,2:07:34.82,*Default,,0,0,0,,他们试图找出杀死弗雷迪的凶手.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}They've been trying to flush out Freddie's killer.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:34.86,2:07:39.17,*Default,,0,0,0,,- 你开玩笑.   - 他们给了我这个假期,\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- You're kidding.  - They're giving me this vacation,{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:39.18,2:07:40.45,*Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我为什么打扮成这样的缘故.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}which is why the getup.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:40.49,2:07:43.36,*Default,,0,0,0,,这也是你为什么没听到我的消息.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}Which is why you haven't heard from me.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:43.45,2:07:45.44,*Default,,0,0,0,,你知道, 整个世界都认为是你杀了弗雷迪.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}You know, the whole world thinks you killed Freddie.{\c}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:45.52,2:07:48.21,*Default,,0,0,0,,-哦!太可怕了.   -我知道.\N{\fnTahoma\fs14\c&H00ffff&\3c&H000000&}- Oh ! It's terrible.  - I know.{\c}
